{"page":5,"prev_page_endpoint":"http://api.change.org/v1/petitions/1459961/reasons?page=4&page_size=500","next_page_endpoint":null,"total_pages":5,"reasons":[{"created_at":"2014-04-28T21:42:11Z","content":"This is important to me because I'm a woman.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Bezanson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22025523"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T22:48:20Z","content":"I believe passionately that all women should have easy access to abortion services if they want them.  No matter where in the world they live.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stephanie Scott","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/72985821"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T02:24:21Z","content":"I am a woman. I have a right to make decisions about my body and my life, and they will be respected. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Julia Downie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89423593"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T01:17:01Z","content":"By not providing women with access to the medical procedures they may not only want, but need, is denying them of their human rights-- something that Canada, as a country, and New Brunswick, as a province, is obligated to protect. Abortion was not made illegal in New Brunswick, but it almost may as well have been. The fact that women are only funded in abortion if approved by two doctors is a rule made for black and white decision making, something the healthcare is not. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carlie Fyfe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89315525"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T21:16:33Z","content":"La femme doit avoir le droit de choisir.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Louise Richard","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89668990"},{"created_at":"2014-04-16T23:50:58Z","content":"Hello?  It is 2014, not 1965.... women have a right to choose, male politicians and religious people do not have the right to choose for us!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Debbie McKeil","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/60800840"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T20:11:44Z","content":"The closure of this clinic affects not women not only in New Brunswick, but across the Maritimes. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hannah Munday","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12769781"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T15:01:53Z","content":"equality. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"catherine macneil","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/44594461"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T19:11:32Z","content":"I am human and I believe in the freedom of choice","like_count":0,"author_name":"Melanie Melanson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89394782"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T19:23:44Z","content":"Because I believe that women should be entitled to choose their options, and this has been unfairly decided upon by men. This is from a young man who believes women need the only say in decisions that only affect them.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Devon McAllister","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78387639"},{"created_at":"2014-05-08T00:33:29Z","content":"It's important that we continue to fight for reproductive justice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sandra-Lynn Leclaire","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35725473"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T14:17:01Z","content":"Abortion access is a human right. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Ackermann","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6926218"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T13:45:39Z","content":"Accessibility for these woman is important!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lauren McCallum","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78381890"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T22:20:18Z","content":"Our body's, our choice","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christa Martin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89295049"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T23:30:35Z","content":"Reproductive rights are human rights.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jocelyn Hebert","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3594613"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T22:26:11Z","content":"This is EXTREMELY important to me because I, as well as every other woman in this province (and country), should have the right to have an abortion if we need to. I cannot afford a child, nor will I be able to afford an abortion if the need ever arises, and I am certain that many women are in the same boat as I am.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sabrina Poirier","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85351478"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T21:55:37Z","content":"As a female practicing in health care, I believe all women should have equal rights to medical care including safe termination of pregnancy.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hyehyun Paek","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89788297"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T22:56:00Z","content":"access to abortion should exist in NB","like_count":0,"author_name":"Susan Guravich","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89676317"},{"created_at":"2014-04-28T02:10:57Z","content":"This petition is not based on reality. Women in this province have access to abortions when medically necessary for free. There is no reason to pay a private clinic for this service.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bert Fakename","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/90979275"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T02:17:25Z","content":"Women in NB should have the same right to choose as any across Canada","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ken Holyoke","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/60778701"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T17:07:49Z","content":"Abortion is a right in Canada and not one that should be impeded by small minded individuals who think that rape is the only reason to have an abortion. The Social Determinants of Health show that poverty is a barrier to healthcare and, in Canada, poverty should not prevent you from getting the care you need. Abortions should be covered for all patients across the entire country. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Maegan Springman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2494312"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T11:20:27Z","content":"A violation of human rights in Canada is a misnomer! It's absolutely ridiculous that this is even happening! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Margaret Piercey","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85275392"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T13:47:03Z","content":"Women have the right to decide what happens to their own bodies, this should not be a right that is exclusively available to women who are able to pay for it. This is not only a women's reproductive health rights issue but an issue of equality. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jessica Lyon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85290042"},{"created_at":"2014-05-05T16:51:02Z","content":"Women must always have a choice!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rachel  Schooley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/4998642"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T19:47:38Z","content":"A woman's right to choose matters. Also, we do not need more abused/neglected children turned out into society. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kara McCarthy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89397778"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T21:27:28Z","content":"women should have the right to chose ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shelby Mcintyre","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3575746"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T22:26:50Z","content":"Indeed no one's rights should be open for debate, let alone denied.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Elisabeth Caron","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/465609"},{"created_at":"2014-03-25T14:33:05Z","content":"I went several times in NB, love the place, work for woman rights in France, matters to me","like_count":0,"author_name":"Clementine Hahn","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87278057"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T22:59:30Z","content":"Because it is wrong that as a woman I have no power over my own body ","like_count":0,"author_name":"charla macneil","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66616452"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T00:50:02Z","content":"Legal right to choose is all but taken away when a safe facility is not available. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"erin price","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/4996214"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T22:37:29Z","content":"They women have to have access to this right . This is an emergency need ","like_count":0,"author_name":"MARISA ROJAS","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78588877"},{"created_at":"2014-04-16T00:53:17Z","content":"woman's right! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Julie Laplante","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89802262"},{"created_at":"2014-04-22T13:18:34Z","content":"My body, my choice. Women already go through a lot when they are deciding whether or not to have an abortion, we don't need the government telling us when, where and how much! This clinic helps people and needs to stay open.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shanna Dechaine","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/90404879"},{"created_at":"2014-03-17T15:12:13Z","content":"All Canadian women have a right to safe access to abortion and control over their lives and their bodies.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Denise MacDonald","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10486523"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T02:24:28Z","content":"human rights are everybody's rights","like_count":0,"author_name":"noah soroka","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89689513"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T12:45:14Z","content":"because people deserve to have the choice, whether you believe in what they are doing or not, does not matter, what give anyone else the right to make that choice for them. lets take our heads out of the stone age and grow up a little","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tyler Matchett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89361085"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T15:55:43Z","content":"Because a woman's reproductive rights belong to the woman, not me, not any religious group and not to any government. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marlene Tompkins","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85169842"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T10:40:19Z","content":"We need free Abortion on demand ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Janice Catherall","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12654027"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T21:27:29Z","content":"There should be more accessibility and definitely the OPTION!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Krista Knorr","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89287468"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T21:13:41Z","content":"Pro choice ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stefanie Grana","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89404557"},{"created_at":"2014-03-31T19:15:23Z","content":"These services are important to all women who wish to have the right to decide what goes on in their own bodies. That right shouldn't change dependant on whether you can afford to pay for the care or not.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Allison Green","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/88029934"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T23:26:30Z","content":"Everyone should have a choice, people make mistakes, but at a young age why make them raise a child when they cant provide for them and are not ready. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brittany Woodford","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89307081"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T19:50:07Z","content":"Women should have the option to make the choice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Greg Richard","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/57369008"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:07:03Z","content":"Reproductive rights are human rights.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Andrew O'Brien","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89373710"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T15:56:31Z","content":"Women should have safe access to all medical procedures; their health should not be at risk because it clashes with oppressive ideologies.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Adriana Alfano","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/26913529"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T18:26:17Z","content":"Respect for women's choices and health.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lorna Cairns","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/67539111"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T16:22:55Z","content":"Women need to have safe access to abortions in NB. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Angela Nicholson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89628995"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T21:13:42Z","content":"abortion clinics should be available to anyone who requires them. There should be more clinics, and it's absolutely crazy that this one is closing!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Danielle H","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55976922"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T18:25:17Z","content":"We must care for all women. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Joanne Hogeveen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89475760"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T20:31:30Z","content":"Considering the antiquated law in this province regarding access to hospital abortions this clinic is absolutely necessary.  As a woman this is  safety net service that one hopes to never need to use.  I have had two friends who have gone to this clinic in bad situations.  They are so kind there and made sure they knew all of the options available other then abortion.  Only one of my friends got an abortion but both got help that they desperately needed.  To lose this clinic would me a major step back for our province.  Women should not been left holding the bag on the cost of these services.  Nothing good will come of increasing the number of children born into homes that are not ready for them emotionally, not wanting to bring children into an unstable/abusive home situation and forcing women many of whom took other preventive measures to carry a child they do not want.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Emily Legacy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/62074435"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T10:27:41Z","content":"All women should have access to safe, free and informed birth control. This includes abortion.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amelie Bryar","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89715838"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T19:06:34Z","content":"It is not by reducing CHOICES that we will attain freedom, happiness and equality. I believe it is extremely important to keep Morgentaler Clinic alive to better suit the needs of the people involved in complex situations. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Julie Belliveau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89268481"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T18:30:26Z","content":"Reproductive health should be covered by the government. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Polly Leonard","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7327244"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T19:51:06Z","content":"Reproductive rights!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cynthia Cheng","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/44529537"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T19:08:49Z","content":"It's of the utmost importance for women to have a choice and options, and not be limited due to socioeconomic factors.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Courtney Veal","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85197539"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T16:51:31Z","content":"protecting women's rights is important","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gerarda Despres","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/80551556"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T17:27:53Z","content":"Give women the right to choose, and help the one's in need.  That is what our rights are for.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mooky Khalil","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89754260"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T18:39:52Z","content":"It should be a basic right for women to have safe and easy access to this service, outside the impossibly rigid regulations for a hospital to perform an abortion.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Scott Dubreuil","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/51477918"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T15:10:24Z","content":"Our choice, not the government.  Having unwanted children that a mother can't afford to have (and/or doesn't want) is a burden to the tax system not a boon and terrible for mental health.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Vanessa Kavanagh","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89532594"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T21:45:46Z","content":"IT'S THE LAW! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hilary Morgan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31954339"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T17:31:12Z","content":"Every pregnancy should be a wanted pregnancy. A policy which limits access to abortions to those with sufficient income and the relevant social connections is deplorable.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gary Bowden","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89540939"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T04:11:53Z","content":"We need to improve access for women in the Maritime provinces, not reduce it!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kate N","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10167870"},{"created_at":"2014-03-15T16:22:37Z","content":"We should all have the power to have control over our own bodies without money being a factor","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bethany Scott","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30370817"},{"created_at":"2014-04-06T00:41:55Z","content":"Women's health is important to everyone","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kristopher Dodd","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56459840"},{"created_at":"2014-04-24T13:34:57Z","content":"This is about women's rights to make choices about their bodies - this is a human right. It is a duty of our healthcare system and our government to provide safe and accessible abortion clinics.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Robyn Beninger","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/90642985"},{"created_at":"2014-05-05T14:51:53Z","content":"Because having choice, is about having access!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Makeda Zook","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13030919"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T17:55:49Z","content":"I am pro choice it should be my right to choose.  I don't think the government should pay for it but it should be available if someone feels that they need it","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shirley McIntyre","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55434686"},{"created_at":"2014-04-28T18:23:45Z","content":"Abortions don't stop by shutting down clinics or taking away their funding. We have seen this throughout history. Nor should they. In 2014 it is time to start sending the message that women's health and safety is EVERYONE'S health and safety as they are the core of every society and their choice over their bodies should be at the forefront of health care everywhere. Restricting access to abortions is taking away a fundamental human right. Shame on you NB. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Vanessa Cicchino","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22596247"},{"created_at":"2014-04-27T15:33:53Z","content":"Women need to have access to abortion services, in order to preserve their mental and physical health.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Francine deMontigny","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/21575666"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T22:57:33Z","content":"because people should have the right to chose what they do. if they cant take are of the child and they feel its the only way then let them do it","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ally Sharpe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89301486"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T23:43:11Z","content":"Everyone should have access to abortions. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"breanna kato","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2290704"},{"created_at":"2014-03-24T19:32:48Z","content":"Every Canadian woman should have the choice of her life.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Francine Chaine","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87190853"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T16:03:16Z","content":"It is disgusting that some women in Canada in 2014 aren't given the right to decide what is right or wrong for their lives and their bodies. This is a huge step backward for women's rights in New Brunswick and it is not acceptable. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cheyenne Coates","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89378566"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T15:17:39Z","content":"Because NB Has set back women by being pig headed","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jeremy Macaulay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89621803"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T18:20:28Z","content":"Je trouve ind\u00e9cent, en 2014, que l'axais \u00e0 l'avortement, sans avoir \u00e0 subir de jugements, ne soit pas offert dans ma province!  Puis, la province devrait payer pour ce qui est un droit qui n'est plus \u00e0 contest\u00e9. Cette clinique est une n\u00e9ss\u00e9cit\u00e9, d'autant plus qu'elle est l'avenue la moins couteuse pour les femmes de l'I.P.E.. La vie de plusieurs femmes est mise en danger par un m\u00e9pris d'une autres \u00e9poque. Ne fermez pas les yeux, il faux s'unir par respect et amour, oui, amour des femmes! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Robert Blanchard","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36016627"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T22:31:04Z","content":"Half of the population are women, we have the right to choose what's best for us. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Maite Cristina Loria Lopez","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/53525514"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T17:46:59Z","content":"While I am personally pro-life and believe there are more options than terminating a pregnancy, the damages to women that happen from improper abortions (which history has shown occurs in areas and times where illegal abortion is enforced) are far to great to make access to one as restricted as this.  If we believe in universal healthcare, as our government funds with our tax dollars, then we are required to make sure the women who make the choice to undergo these procedures are safe and cared for in a proper manner.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Johnathan Hossack","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89261350"},{"created_at":"2014-03-28T19:52:30Z","content":"I believe women should have the right to decide what happens to their body, and I honestly think that no woman wants an abortion, but they deserve to be able to get them if they feel the need.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mitchell Kadolph","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87766492"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T19:06:32Z","content":"Because it's about time women have equal rights. It's appalling that it's 2014 and that still hasn't been achieved.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Emily Doody","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85197111"},{"created_at":"2014-04-28T20:20:59Z","content":"This exploits the inability of those women unable to afford the fee.  Not fair.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mel Lucas","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/70237283"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T00:18:30Z","content":"Women's reproductive rights should be important to everyone","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ben Salmon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89311390"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T20:09:42Z","content":"Pro-choice for women's bodies.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Katelyn Hogenbirk","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89776598"},{"created_at":"2014-03-21T15:49:35Z","content":"I don't care if you, yourself, are pro-life. That does not give you the right to make the decision for somebody else. Funding abortions does NOT mean you have to get one but that people who really do need one can have safe and assured access to the service.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Tooley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/79747180"},{"created_at":"2014-03-26T13:56:11Z","content":"I believe that women's reproductive rights should be considered a priority to the government of New Brunswick. Therefore, I believe that the government should fund services at the Morgentaler Clinic in Fredericton, NB.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Genevi\u00e8ve Boily","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/71976662"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T22:55:56Z","content":"Hey New Brunswick, we're tired of your shit. We demand accessible government funded abortion. Now. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Keri Ryan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89558830"},{"created_at":"2014-03-24T22:16:03Z","content":"right for women to choose","like_count":0,"author_name":"Catherine Dube","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87208598"},{"created_at":"2014-04-16T23:09:54Z","content":"Its a legal right, and a moral obligation.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brent Evered","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89941222"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T10:32:25Z","content":"Women must have the right to choose when it come to such an important issue.  The government must to forced to comply with the law.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Barry MacKnight","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89606294"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T12:51:07Z","content":"I support a woman's right to choose no matter where she may live in Canada. The New Brunswick provincial government is infringing upon women's rights by impeding easy access to safe and legal abortion despite what David Alward and his government may believe. A woman's body is her own; why should the provincial government force a woman to carry a baby to term that she does not want? What kind of life is waiting for that child? Keep every pregnancy a wanted one. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Justin MacLean","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89617879"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T16:33:49Z","content":"This is law - all women need to have access to Health Care in Canada.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rose Allen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78438454"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T23:44:45Z","content":"It is appalling that the PEI and NB gov't s do not fund abortions in private clinics and yet have set up additional hurdles re doctor referrals (not based in law) for woman seeking hospital abortions. I am so grateful for all the Morgentaler clinic has done to support Island women over the years.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alice Crook","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89414953"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T19:14:23Z","content":"... because whether a person if pro-life or pro-choice and woman's rights should not be ridiculed and decided upon by a group of middle aged white men who don't know the severity of their actions. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gina Hyson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89649903"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T23:04:32Z","content":"It's my body and it's my choice when, and if, I will or will not have a baby. I was a foster child, now I am a forty-ish woman, with a degree in structural social work; I have expertise as a scientist in addition to a lifetime of lived experience on this subject. Limiting choices will undeniably lead to an increase in unplanned pregnancies resulting in babies born who may severely suffer the fate of being unwanted children, and I can assure you, NO ONE should EVER have to live that way.\r\nOur child protective services and foster care system in Canada is already overburdened. The numbers of Crown Wards/foster kids/adopted children who become statistics in \"the system\" under the category of child deaths reported in Western provinces is shocking. It's sickening that any provincial/federal government would even think about making such a stupid decision. Think about the human cost - the emotional damage it does to a child who has lived, knowing they are not wanted by their parent(s). Or unloved. Unwelcome. Neglected. Abused.\r\n\r\nHow long would you live before you start seriously considering suicide?\r\n \r\nI think abortion clinics are a necessity in Canada. We are a multi-cultural country, and you must consider how immigrants may view an unwanted pregnancy - for example, a 20 year-old, unmarried Muslim woman - how do you think her parents/siblings may respond?I think by not funding abortion clinics in New Brunswick, and the rest of Canada, it demonstrates a total lack of understanding of long-term economic impact the tax-payer is burdened with. Refusing to initiate, or pulling away existing funding from any abortion clinic(s) in New Brunswick, when this is already the poorest province in the country is not economically advantageous for us. New Brunswickers will be making a very expensive mistake to oppose abortion clinics - it is the government's responsibility to explain why this is needed in our society today. We are not living in the early 1900's, we need to keep up with reality in our legal process and government processes, if we want to advance naturally in our education, health and social progression. Otherwise, this government has done a great disservice to the people it represents, and has put us behind even farther than we are now. Shame.\r\nFoolish policies demonstrate fools in government. \r\nSmarten up, please.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Zai K.","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/59814402"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T23:44:46Z","content":"It's a big deal to me; I have many friends in NB that this would be effecting. Women should have their rights. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ashleigh Feltmate","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89308988"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T14:31:03Z","content":"Women's rights are fundamental to a free and open society.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Graham MacVannel","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89460684"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T02:22:31Z","content":"I have many friends who this would affect, and I strongly believe in a woman having the right to her own body.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Joe Purcell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89582681"},{"created_at":"2014-04-16T23:09:54Z","content":"I was raised in an extremely religious household, where it was taught that abortion is a sin against God. I not only grew up believing this but also believed that this was popular belief. The problem is that pro-life members are more comfortable speaking out. Pro-choicers are not. I am pro choice and I am ready to speak up. New Brunswick women need this support. Women no longer need to be shamed for taking control of their lives and their bodies.","like_count":0,"author_name":"colleen kerby","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89941218"},{"created_at":"2014-04-03T13:30:08Z","content":"Notre corps nous appartient - ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carmelle Lecompte","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/88338824"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T23:26:01Z","content":"NO woman should have to be disscriminated against, because of being part of lower class and not being able to afford an abortion, and being FORCED into proceeding in a pregnancy she does not want.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kiara Durelle","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85357152"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T01:47:56Z","content":"Women should have the right to control their own body and their future.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jim Gallant","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2107867"},{"created_at":"2014-03-25T00:16:15Z","content":"Abortion must be offer to anyone  who want it, without any problem","like_count":0,"author_name":"Evelyne Desaulniers","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87216576"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T21:13:35Z","content":"It is unacceptable that you are infringing upon these women's rights to body autonomy. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jill MacIntyre","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/44463315"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:25:11Z","content":"freedom","like_count":0,"author_name":"Laura Levesque","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89375229"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T19:03:37Z","content":"This is important to me because I am a woman who needs to have a voice for her reproductive rights. Living in fear of not being able to attain a safe abortion in the future is terrifying. I never want to see my fellow friends and family be forced to have an unwanted pregnancy and or worse try to hurt themselves in hopes to have a miscarriage. NB Fredericton needs this wonderful place. I have been a volunteer escort with this clinic for the past four amazing years. It will be a dark day for women when this beautiful places closes its doors. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kerri Wood","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15468333"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T17:00:27Z","content":"This clinic is one the only reasonable options for women on PEI closing this clinic won't only have an effect on NB women but also PEI women too. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rebecca Chapman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/44742935"},{"created_at":"2014-04-18T12:50:48Z","content":" a woman should have the right to choose.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Krista Gilliss","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/90095656"},{"created_at":"2014-03-09T20:14:47Z","content":"In a country where women's rights over their bodies seems [surprisingly] tenuous, we need to protect a woman's right to choose and ensure services are accessible.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Maggie Crain","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/61356395"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T14:52:19Z","content":"All women across Canada must have access to safe and legal abortion. The federal and provincial governments must ensure this fundamental right.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cynthia Hammond","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36887410"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T16:02:03Z","content":"Access to health services for women should be available across our country.  It is shameful New Brunswick would restrict these services and in violation of the Court's ruling. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Pat Rowantree","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89535510"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T23:23:12Z","content":"This is a MEDICAL PROCEDURE. Such operations should be covered by tax dollars, and thus not be restricted to those fortunate enough to afford them. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Karsten Saunders","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85228634"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T19:45:26Z","content":"Every woman deserves access to safe, funded abortions. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cheryl Norrad","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89548776"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T03:28:09Z","content":"This will cause more harm to the women of our community. Rape victims, women in abusive relationships, failed birth control ect. are going to have to find other ways to abort unwated pregnancies, very unsafe and unhealthy ways. If women can't afford to spend the $700 to abort a pregnancy how are they going to afford to raise a child? Buying a crib can cost more than $700. This will also hurt the unwanted children by being brought into unstable environments, living without food, diapers and love. Mr. David Alward I will plead to you to help our community, if it was not for an abortion and I had 6 years ago, at this clinic, I wouldn't have my beautiful daughter that I have today nor would I be married in a healthy loving relationship. What you choose to do will seriously affect women's lives and futures the choice is up to you on wether you will help the women of your community or disadvantage them.\r\n\r\nThank you for reading.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kayla O'Neill","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89324181"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T01:13:12Z","content":"As women, we have the right to an abortion and it's wrong that our access is being even more limited than it already is. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amy Schmidt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89563966"},{"created_at":"2014-03-26T17:32:56Z","content":"It's our right.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Malika Rogosin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87454160"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T16:40:26Z","content":"#ProChoice","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jillian Miner","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89256690"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T18:27:56Z","content":"Sexual health is an important part of a womans overall health and so is her decision to plan a family at her own rate. Womens uteruses are NOT up for debate.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Loreen Smith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29848681"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T16:55:13Z","content":"We need to protect women's rights over their own bodies! I have moved away, partially because of continuing crap like this. Please don't get any MORE backwards, New Brunswick! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Monique Aube","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3583161"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T19:25:27Z","content":"access for all women in new brunswick!","like_count":0,"author_name":"jenny burgess","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85200040"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T18:49:43Z","content":"I believe that we are being discriminated and our rights are being violated.  The job for the government is to protect our rights and they have clearly taken a step back in social progress.  Some woman need abortions and its our body, our choice, respect that! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Grasse","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78449469"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T22:50:35Z","content":"There is no reason that women in this province shouldn't have access to health care - it is incredibly distressing that the Clinic will be closing and as a province we should be ashamed that we let it get to this point. \u201cNo woman can call herself free until she can choose consciously whether she will or will not be a mother.\u201d Margaret Sanger","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kate Doyle","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3582053"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T01:04:36Z","content":"This is 100% unacceptable. UNACCEPTABLE!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Emily Duff","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35924236"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T00:51:08Z","content":"It's a woman's RIGHT!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marta MacQuarrie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45916201"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T22:38:20Z","content":"as a doctor in nb I know how this service is needed.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rene Robichaud","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89675050"},{"created_at":"2014-04-16T21:49:32Z","content":"Because closing the only clinic discriminates against most lower-income women and families, who are not exactly a tiny minority in our province.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Judith Weiss","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11424691"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T17:24:02Z","content":"Access to health care is my human right and I do not believe that the government should control what I do with my body. My reproductive health should be a priority!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Elizabeth Harrop-Archibald","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85182156"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T15:31:19Z","content":"Les femmes doivent avoir le plein contr\u00f4le sur leur vie et avoir acc\u00e8s aux soins de sant\u00e9, quels qu'ils soient. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marie-\u00c8ve Muller","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89742583"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T21:05:03Z","content":"For me, this is a civil rights no-brainer. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"peter sutherland","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2608921"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T20:11:03Z","content":"We need to stop punishing women for having sex, and also thinking that because you can't have a child somehow other people should therefore not be able to abort.  Crazy.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alison Belyea","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89659535"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T19:45:28Z","content":"Choice is important, the law allows so the service should be available.","like_count":0,"author_name":"K. David Woolley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36411568"},{"created_at":"2014-05-04T21:19:16Z","content":"CHOICE.","like_count":0,"author_name":"rachel levine","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58119192"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T16:31:12Z","content":"Reproductive health is an important part of overall maternal health. Maternal health options shouldn't be limited.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Allison Crinkley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/61297765"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T11:27:34Z","content":"Choice! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jill Calder","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89720576"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T11:56:36Z","content":"Important medical service that must be offered in an already medically underserved community.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jason Bonar","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89613566"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T18:30:30Z","content":"It should be important to everyone. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kyra Baldwin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85191142"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T04:05:21Z","content":"because everyone should have a choice. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"kathy kilpatrick","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30761425"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T21:57:04Z","content":"I'm a woman.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lisa Walker","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/17192814"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T02:04:17Z","content":"Becasue my personal choice shouldn't infringe on another persons choice.  Oh, and Canadians have a nice little document called the Canadian Charter of Rights and Freedoms (section seven is a great read!).","like_count":0,"author_name":"Fiona Thom","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85369008"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T13:51:40Z","content":"I was born and raised in Nb and I believe this is a huge step back for the Province!! You are not taking away the need only removing the means, Women will find other ways and by doing so harming themselves and only causing more issues and taking up more of the \"tax payers dollars\". ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Courtney Best","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/79372288"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T19:31:00Z","content":"Women deserve bodily autonomy more than fundamentalist pseudo-Christians deserve the peace of mind that restricted access to abortions will bring them. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mark Pott","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89271085"},{"created_at":"2014-03-26T03:31:02Z","content":"Women's right","like_count":0,"author_name":"Minh Thi Nguyen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69002836"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T20:17:38Z","content":"I'm a guy and I find this outrageous ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jeff Parent","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52162373"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T00:59:57Z","content":"The Morgentaler clinic saves women's lives. A woman's right to choose is incredibly important, but the ability to exercise that right is also important. We NEED to make sure that women can continue to access these life saving services.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shireen Noble","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2609067"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T21:03:12Z","content":"ALL Canadian women should have equal access to healthcare across the nation.  NB and PEI should be ashamed!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jessica Murray","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27378170"},{"created_at":"2014-03-25T19:10:17Z","content":"All of Canada funds abortion clinics as it is under the Canada Health Act that they do so. New Brunswick, however, refuses to, it's time to step up and fund the Morgentaler Clinic.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tiffany Howe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47265377"},{"created_at":"2014-03-17T16:19:10Z","content":"It's important for all women, and all Canadian citizens.  Not only is abortion a necessary service (confirmed by the SCC in 1988), but it is outrageous that a province continues to flout the Canada Health Act without suffering any consequences.The only ones who suffer are the women of New Brunswick.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Debby Copes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52695153"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T04:19:29Z","content":"Women's Rights. Choice should be an option for every individual. This issue is extremely important.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Allery Safruk","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89591190"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T21:42:15Z","content":"Because I am a woman from New Brunswick and this is not right.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amanda Ellis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/88505315"},{"created_at":"2014-03-26T14:22:29Z","content":"Every woman deserves a choice, whether she was a victim of sexual assault or not. Having a child is a life-changing decision and it SHOULD BE a decision.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amanda Rundle","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87427846"}]}
