{"page":1,"prev_page_endpoint":null,"next_page_endpoint":"http://api.change.org/v1/petitions/1459961/reasons?page=2&page_size=500","total_pages":5,"reasons":[{"created_at":"2014-03-12T00:21:05Z","content":"As a woman and a future doctor in the New Brunswick health system, this is something that is particularly close to heart. I plan to make it my professional goal to do away with all such patriarchal laws when this becomes my field to advocate. For now adding my name to the thousands of others will suffice.","like_count":21,"author_name":"Christine Crain","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2518872"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T00:08:45Z","content":"Provide universal access to safe medical abortions to all the women of Canada in order that every pregnancy  is  wanted pregnancy","like_count":18,"author_name":"Dr Norm Barwin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8917735"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T15:19:05Z","content":"My rights should not be up for debate and should be the same all across Canada. My financial situation should not determine whether or not I can access important healthcare.","like_count":18,"author_name":"Heather Elliott","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6119"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T11:50:13Z","content":"medical reasons are not the only important ones for an abortion being necessary","like_count":12,"author_name":"Andrew Sullivan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31965045"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T16:22:50Z","content":"Fredericton was where I began my career as a law professor. Both my children were born in Fredericton.  I love New Brunswick and have long grieved the choices government has made, choices that do not respect the range of women's needs and choices.  It is time for change","like_count":8,"author_name":"Rebecca Johnson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37915911"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T02:48:16Z","content":"Every child a wanted child and every mother a willing mother. ","like_count":6,"author_name":"Miriam Jones","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2663339"},{"created_at":"2014-03-14T23:46:04Z","content":"Denial of equitable access to health care services based on sex - only women have abortions - and socioeconomic status is reprehensible. Not only is charging a fee for abortion illegal, as it contravenes the Morgentaler Supreme Court decision of 1988 and the Canada Health Act, it undermines the constitutional rights and freedoms of women and serves as a barrier that further marginalizes those who are already in a vulnerable and precarious socioeconomic position. Free access to family planning tools is essential to improving the standard of living for women, their families, and communities. For taxpayers, the financial costs associated with compliance with the Morgentaler Supreme Court decision of 1988 and the Canada Health Act are negligible when compared with the ongoing economic and societal burdens that result from depriving women of the right to delay motherhood until such time as they feel that they are mentally, physically, and financially prepared.\r\nThe Office of Foreign Affairs, Trade and Development Canada have set \u201cPromote Gender Equality and Empower Women\u201d, \u201cImprove Maternal Health\u201d, and \u201cEradicate Extreme Poverty and Hunger\u201d as Millennium Development Goals for 2015. All are laudable goals that will help to make our world a better place for everyone in it. Let\u2019s try to accomplish these goals right here in Canada by eliminating the illegal financial barriers to reproductive health services.\r\n","like_count":5,"author_name":"Holly Saunders","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58275502"},{"created_at":"2014-03-26T15:53:22Z","content":"I am a doctor.  I practise abortions every week.  I am also a woman.  And I want my rigths to be respected.","like_count":5,"author_name":"Genevi\u00e8ve Verret","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87440905"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T11:47:46Z","content":"I believe in choice. 90%+ men make the choice of walking away from their pregnant teenage partners. When women have babies too young,they need to forgo education-thus assigning them and their children to a lifetime of poverty. Biology does not give women equal opportunity to walk away from the error of an unplanned birth. If law does not force men to be parents by being financially responsible for the care of a baby,then women need the choice of abortion.","like_count":5,"author_name":"Roxanne Kasdan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85404659"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T20:26:58Z","content":"Abortion is a right of any female who wants/needs one; not only for the privileged few who can afford the procedure- much like every other medical procedure in Canada, abortions should be relatively free. This needs to change. Everyone should sign the shit out of this petition.","like_count":4,"author_name":"Emma Howell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85336090"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T01:21:40Z","content":"I shouldn't be asked why it's important, it just is. Every women deserves the right to an adoration if she needs one or not.","like_count":3,"author_name":"Destiny Paul","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29048931"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T19:16:49Z","content":"Women's rights are human rights. Simple. Think twice about silencing the voices of those who made the life you live  possible. ","like_count":3,"author_name":"Caely Dunlop","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85326876"},{"created_at":"2014-03-09T20:03:10Z","content":"My rights as a woman living in New Brunswick. ","like_count":3,"author_name":"Richelle Martin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78502264"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T18:02:00Z","content":"We are all individuals. We all make our own choices, with our own consequences...no matter the issue. Abortion is a personal  private choice for a woman. Her choice. Her decision. Her consequence. ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Shannon Valanne","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85187283"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T19:04:16Z","content":"Why are we still fighting for these rights my body my right. ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Danette  Bartlett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7483183"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T10:38:55Z","content":"Not only is the NB government's policy unconstitutional. It disproportionately affects women in rural areas and who are economically disadvantaged. Research from the US has shown that when abortion is inaccessible due to financial constraints, women are forced to delay the procedure into a later gestational stages, while they try to obtain enough money.  This is unfair to NB women who deserve respect and accessible reproductive services. ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Cassandra  Morris","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8403380"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T02:00:59Z","content":"Women throughout Canada should have the option to have safe medical interventions, including abortions, funded by universal Medicare.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Peggy berkowitz","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85241071"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T17:19:00Z","content":"It is time that the NB government catches up with the 21st century.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Dan Taylor","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32164757"},{"created_at":"2014-03-09T23:38:29Z","content":"Because reproductive health must be made a priority","like_count":2,"author_name":"Emily McKenzie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/76323668"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T23:24:10Z","content":"Canadian women should have the same rights across the country-  regardless of class, race/ethnicity, religion,  sexuality or geography.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Donelda Mac Donald","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56531690"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T00:21:38Z","content":"Not the church and not the state - women must decide their fate ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Paul Kellogg","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47825954"},{"created_at":"2014-03-09T21:52:09Z","content":"I believe this is an important step in supporting womens reproductive rights. ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Josie Aiello","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85107573"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T11:39:17Z","content":"Every woman as the right to receive safe treatment","like_count":2,"author_name":"Lisa Flower","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/48853491"},{"created_at":"2014-03-09T23:53:29Z","content":"All women deserve equal access to necessary health services - the laws limiting women in NB from obtaining accessible and affordable abortions is in violation of this. ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Amelia Pendleton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12975871"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T22:23:42Z","content":"Medical services should not be decided based on religious views,  personal beliefs or to win political votes.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Nadine Jacskon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56177139"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T16:25:30Z","content":"Women have the right to make the decisions about their bodies and lives without money being a factor","like_count":2,"author_name":"Lindsay Gallagher","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/39347088"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T18:46:06Z","content":"Women should not have to choose between an abortion or rent.  There is also no need for a woman to choose between a life of struggling with an unplanned child, or the pain of having to put them up for adoption when there is no way the mother could support the child.  ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Sarah Michel","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85193622"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T20:05:27Z","content":"Choice saves lives!","like_count":2,"author_name":"Astri Buchanan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/59211878"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T00:03:15Z","content":"Reproductive freedom and bodily autonomy are women's rights. This is a legal, medical procedure and needs to be available to ALL women, not just the ones who can afford it.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Jodi King","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16407922"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T23:41:31Z","content":"Women should be able to make a choice about their body without discrimination. ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Nancy Depow-Mitchell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/68139455"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T16:04:05Z","content":"Women's reproductive rights should be considered a priority to the government of New Brunswick.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Bethany Chandler","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85171199"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T18:29:10Z","content":"It is very important in today's world and economy to provide women with choice.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Tara Hay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12896510"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T20:45:18Z","content":"It is an embarrassment that we even have to sign a petition for this basic healthcare need. Stop abdicating your responsibilities to women, New Brunswick!","like_count":2,"author_name":"Jessica Shaw","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10832139"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T19:24:27Z","content":"Every woman should be able to make her own choice. Economic situations shouldn't be a factor.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Sonja Vojnovic","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85583498"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T19:41:25Z","content":"Discrimination in essential health care is unconstitutional, harms women and creates a climate of fear and shame that further exacerbates these harms. ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Jula Hughes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32429169"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T22:53:51Z","content":"Because it is a woman's right to choose. It will cost far more to the health system to have unwanted pregnancies than to terminate them.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Margo  Sheppard","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/23214650"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T09:29:11Z","content":"Women have a right to safe medical care.  What bothers me is that if men could get pregnant and have their lives turned upside down this wouldn't even be an issue.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Jennifer Jamieson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85143519"},{"created_at":"2014-03-09T22:05:47Z","content":"Every woman should have the right to control what happens in their life and to their body. ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Jasmine Kranat","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85108788"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T20:45:55Z","content":"Abortion services at clinics are covered under Medicare in every province except New Brunswick and PEI. What the New Brunswick politicians are doing is in direct contravention of the spirit of the Canada Health Act.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Allison Brewer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85211936"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T22:19:57Z","content":"Not only is this a violation of human rights, unwanted children impose an enormous financial burden on everyone, especially on those of a lower SES, thereby perpetuating the cycle of poverty.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Andrew Baldanza","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58848376"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T18:34:46Z","content":"Because too many kids end up in FAR worse trouble when it could be avoided if this were an option for them. MUCH needed change! Thank you. ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Candice Green","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85191774"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T19:08:14Z","content":"A women should have more right to what's going on in her body than a political entity does.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Shannon Scott","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3599221"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T03:19:12Z","content":"making abortions out of reach for those in lower socioeconomic statuses continues the cycle of poverty. ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Charlotte Hill","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85246739"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T00:43:07Z","content":"Because I believe women should had the right to choose when it comes to their own reproduction, and I also believe no child should come into this world without a loving framework to support him/her.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Peta Fussell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85234907"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T21:28:10Z","content":"All women should have equal rights & access to abortion. This is not an opinion, it is a fact. Limiting a woman's ability to get an abortion by charging a hefty wage or making it necessary to receive a mandatory (but nearly impossible to attain) doctors note is simply an abomination. ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Megan Bateman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9101365"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T00:37:27Z","content":"I had no idea abortion rights were so restricted. Make New Brunswick comply with the Canada Health Act so that all women have an equal shot in life, regardless of their income.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Kira McLean","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8413615"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T20:38:45Z","content":"I am fed up with the stonewalling by successive governments. You are violating my rights and the rights of all women in New Brunswick.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Emelie Hubert","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/68822497"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T20:42:42Z","content":"Abortion services is part of the natural health care required by women. 1 in 3 Canadian women have required abortions at some point in their lives.  Decisions about when and whether to have children is a fundamental right and a right of all Canadian women. this service, like all other health care services should be funded through our health care system.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Shelly Blanco","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30645512"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T12:50:45Z","content":"Stop illegally discriminating against the women of NB! Long overdue!","like_count":2,"author_name":"Lee Bryan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1678761"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T16:07:12Z","content":"because women should not be forced to compromise on their health care due to financial challenges","like_count":2,"author_name":"Grace Caldwell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85171633"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T13:06:03Z","content":"Nb is far behind the times for women's rights. We are the only province to not publicly fund therapeutic abortion. The amount of young mothers living far bellow the poverty line and children born to mothers who physically, emotionally and financially cannot care for them is staggering.  Take a walk through saint johns riffle range, it will break your heart. Yes Abortion is sad and terribly difficult, but not one person, regardless of religious beliefs can truthfully say that seeing several children born to a mother who does not care for them, a father who abuses them or has left them, children who's only meal is served at the publicly funded school breakfast program, is less tragic. It's far more terrible too see, it's far more of a strain on tax payers dollars, on social well being and the community. It's time for nb to step into a present day mindset. ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Mallory Driscoll","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85158186"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T00:11:46Z","content":"I am ashamed of and angered by the state of reproductive rights in New Brunswick. ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Nicole Slipp","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1933674"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T11:52:11Z","content":"No one should be forced to continue a pregnancy they neither want nor are prepared for. Every woman has the right to safely manage her own sexual and reproductive health.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Lisa  Miller","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/14294669"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T18:52:13Z","content":"Women deserve the right to have abortions and for the medical procedure to be covered by Medicare. ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Kelsey Sellars","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85194652"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T15:57:26Z","content":"Abortion care services are a part of health care and women's health humans.  Placing restrictions on abortion care only risking harming women's health.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Jill Doctoroff","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/53503786"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T10:37:30Z","content":"It's critical to ensure that people produce children at a time when they are able and willing to provide a stable and loving household. It's better for parents, for children, and for our country.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Lisa  Goddard","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/20880825"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T15:19:20Z","content":"until all sperm is ejaculated responsibly, we will always need access to abortions. pregnancy should never be the deciding factor of becoming a parent. our bodies our decision  ","like_count":2,"author_name":"stef dolan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/53122089"},{"created_at":"2014-03-14T23:43:56Z","content":"Equal access to health care for all, without having to fight through a crowd of ignorant hypocrites in order to obtain said care. It is embarrassing that this should even require a petition to be brought to light.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Sarah Brown","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85783035"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T16:37:18Z","content":"i was an teenage mother who was devestated and humiliated by the pregnancy. i was unloved and tried to terminate the pregnancy myself almost seriously injuring myself in the process. it didn't work but i chose to release the infant to the system which i thought they had a waiting family for but i find later was not the case. i have not been able to find my daughter and don't know if she was victimized by a series of foster homes and misery and wish i could have terminated in the first trimester. my mother was mentally ill and i was very traumatized at the time so felt i could not be a good mother. i was terrified of becoming the same kind of mother. \r\n","like_count":2,"author_name":"voni mann","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3608692"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T13:19:28Z","content":"I am not pro-abortion - I am, however, pro-choice... I feel that like any other procedure this should be covered for women that have to make that choice - for whatever reason...  Who am I to decide what is right or wrong for anyone...","like_count":2,"author_name":"Isabelle Doiron","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/20070511"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T21:41:11Z","content":"By choosing not to fund these operations the New Brunswick government puts the health of its citizens in jeopardy. It's a disgusting abnegation of their responsibility. ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Nancy  Edgar","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/17282175"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T05:21:15Z","content":"I feel that women should have autonomy, i.e. self rule over their bodies, and that we should not discriminate against those that cannot afford such a procedure as it is a medical procedure in a country with government funded health care.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Mitchell Nash","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/41271309"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T20:06:46Z","content":"Women's reproductive rights and access to safe, Medicare-covered abortions should not depend on where a woman lives.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Aneke Mendarozqueta","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/33287990"},{"created_at":"2014-03-18T13:13:40Z","content":"Why should NB women have to pay more? This is discrimination.","like_count":1,"author_name":"emily rutledge","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1264776"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T18:24:21Z","content":"because I believe in a woman's right to choose. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"kathy lewis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11194530"},{"created_at":"2014-03-23T12:00:15Z","content":"A woman's body = a women's  choice","like_count":1,"author_name":"Anne Brown","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87037835"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T22:23:22Z","content":"Everyone should have the right to make their own choices. If a woman is unprepared (whether financially, mentally, or for any other reason) to become a mother, she should have the option to terminate a pregnancy. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Emily Leonard","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/59067310"},{"created_at":"2014-03-22T11:48:15Z","content":"Life as a mom is full of challenges even when you have planned for a child. Let's not force a women to live with a baby which she was not ready for. Women who have been assaulted or despite using contraceptives, became pregnant, already suffer from what happened to them or realize they simply have no way of supporting a child. Please don't take this option from them. Life as a mother is a huge commitment which one must be ready for.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Emily Scott","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86941880"},{"created_at":"2014-03-19T09:28:42Z","content":"Because girls and woman are more than incubators and brood mares.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Candice Heyward-Spence","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1249993"},{"created_at":"2014-04-01T18:46:22Z","content":"Women deserve health care in all areas, including reproductive health. Women have sex, and sometimes pregnancy occurs even if precautions are taken. A woman has not consented to pregnancy just because she has consented to sex. NB's current policies appear to deliberately make it more difficult for women to obtain abortions, as well as prolong what is in reality a time-sensitive issue. These policies need to change in order to give women more access to abortions when they need them.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Lauren Johnson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/88143698"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T18:53:09Z","content":"Everyone should have the freedom to their body and have the same opportunities regardless of socioeconomic status ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Nitanis Bradley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85450333"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T19:39:51Z","content":"Without the Morgentaler clinic, women will have to travel to Montreal for a procedure. This will automatically disadvantage many women who struggle financially. This will add another level of burden, and make abortions only accessible to women in higher income brackets. Freedom of choice should not be tied to one's financial status. Keep the Clinic in Fredericton. New Brunswick should be moving AHEAD, not backwards. \r\n","like_count":1,"author_name":"Heather Todd","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22142971"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T02:18:46Z","content":"The NB Government has absolutely NO right to play politics with women's reproductive rights. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"NJ Baker","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/57345967"},{"created_at":"2014-03-17T23:28:16Z","content":"Women's Reproductive Rights shouldn't be expensive! ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Gillian Smith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52832324"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T00:19:04Z","content":"All basic human rights are important to me. No one should have a monopoly over / the power to control someone else's body. No way, no how. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Shawn Seeley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3568108"},{"created_at":"2014-03-18T02:37:06Z","content":"Women have been given the right to make a choice in this matter. Allow them to be free to actually do so. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Emily Murray","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86385797"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T21:34:55Z","content":"Everybody should have a choice, no matter how much money they have or don't have","like_count":1,"author_name":"Freyja Jokulsdottir","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85469331"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T00:40:54Z","content":"While this is not something that I would personally choose I do not feel that I, nor any other person should have the right to tell a woman what she can and cannot do with her body. A woman's reproductive choices are hers and they should be treated with respect and no judgement. It is far past due for the Government of New Brunswick to stop pushing their agenda and respecting every woman's reproductive rights. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Maureen Wallace","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85485607"},{"created_at":"2014-03-15T01:54:46Z","content":"Women who are considering an abortion should not have to worry about covering the costs of the procedure.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Tabatha Cyrus","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85790534"},{"created_at":"2014-03-19T18:26:38Z","content":"Every woman has the right to make this decision on her own. Furthermore, the Supreme Court has already made the ruling that these restrictions are unconstitutional, so it's about time the New Brunswick government make the appropriate changes!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Isabelle Agnew","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2606676"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T17:59:35Z","content":"Pro Choice ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Jordan Priest","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/51449314"},{"created_at":"2014-03-18T16:07:28Z","content":"All women no matter their age or reason should have the right to this choice.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Catherine McGinnis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86459924"},{"created_at":"2014-03-23T15:24:26Z","content":"This empowers women who need this kind of services in my community.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Bina Sharma","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87055592"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T00:02:29Z","content":"Access should be available across Canada. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Heather McKend","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/65037484"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T21:26:45Z","content":"My partner and I were lucky to enjoy the services of the Morgentaler Clinic located in Ottawa, ON a few years ago.  This health service is vital in our community and should be provided to all Canadians and covered under their corresponding Provincial Health Care.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Yannick Marcerou","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30489782"},{"created_at":"2014-03-27T22:37:44Z","content":"It is quite simply a violation of human rights to deny women access to abortion. You should face criminal action in the course for this violation of the rights of half of all Canadians. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Carolyn McLuskie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/20757549"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T22:29:32Z","content":"Abortion services are women's health services and thus must always be safe, legal, and financially accessible. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Annick MacAskill","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22307214"},{"created_at":"2014-03-18T02:19:12Z","content":"I was almost a 19 year old mother, but I decided that wasn't what I wanted for myself. I fortunately had the means to fund the termination of my pregnancy... but I know many girls that were my age at the time that did not have the same options or opportunities as I did. I've seen so many of my friends and family members had to bare children and raise them even though they didn't want to. This province creates a stigma against a woman's right to choose to bare a child or not... When it is clearly outlined that it is our \"Right.\" Shouldn't our provincial government be protecting and promoting that right? If men had to carry children for the duration of a pregnancy there would be a clinic on every corner, in every airport and shopping mall. With the majority of men VS. women in political authority it is no wonder things are so backwards. I'll be damned if I let a man tell me how to run my life... So why does a male majority government have the authority to dictate what social classes have access to clinics? Who speaks for us? Why are the costs of contraceptives so high, yet if a woman opts for a hysterectomy she is refused, and has to pay for abortions? It looks to me like The New Brunswick government is \"breeding,\" quite an issue. I believe there needs to be some serious sexual health reform in regards to women's rights... Not only with abortions. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Rachel Atkinson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86384525"},{"created_at":"2014-03-25T22:17:56Z","content":"Because every women has the RIGHT to choice when it comes to HER body.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Lacey Corbett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87332209"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T00:45:27Z","content":"Because I should have the choice not to bring up a child in poverty!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Char LeBlanc","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89418226"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T16:03:46Z","content":"Women deserve the right to choose, regardless of income. period.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Marc Gagnon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55391425"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T18:57:32Z","content":"Originally from NB!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Kara Bembridge","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/60800603"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T01:16:34Z","content":"As a young woman trying to finish school and watching all the women who couldn't finish school because of accidental pregnancies and not to mention, for the women who aren't mentally stable to care for a child - Why bring a child in this world if you won't be able to pay for it? ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Kristin Killam","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/76376197"},{"created_at":"2014-03-22T02:47:45Z","content":"As a young New Brunswick woman, I wish that one day we will have our voices heard, and will be able to choose what we do with our own bodies without being shamed or discriminated because of our gender.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Lise A","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/57569463"},{"created_at":"2014-03-19T04:36:26Z","content":"All women should have the right to choose and the access to exercise it, for the sake of human rights and common sense. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Sarah D","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/73269478"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T18:51:17Z","content":"Because I believe that women should have the right to their own bodies, and have the means to have an abortion in the comfort of their own province if they choose. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Desirae Walker","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89266863"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T23:42:25Z","content":"Its a women's right to her own body. Not a churches or any institution.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Jodi Stewart","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85481702"},{"created_at":"2014-04-02T04:39:38Z","content":"Seriously? Approval by two doctors is required? What kind of paternalistic arrangement is this? Women have the right to choose abortion.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Lois Murray","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8461890"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T00:42:15Z","content":"It is our Right as women to be able to decide what to do without the burden of cost.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Samantha Kuhn","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85485682"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T14:53:41Z","content":"This is important to me just like any other right. Things happen, and ALL women should be able to  have access to abortions without having to have it classified as \"medically unfit\". NB is the only province where women have to pay out of their pockets for unwanted pregnancies. Let's step out of the past and into the present!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Emily Dickinson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15850677"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T01:59:13Z","content":"Because women should always have access to choice.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Holly Cairns","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89318309"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T20:57:05Z","content":"Abortion is legal and is a medical procedure so it should be freely available as are other health services in Canada.  A legal service, a legal clinic who is making this problem and what is the motivation?","like_count":1,"author_name":"Brenda Gilbert","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30501867"},{"created_at":"2014-03-17T22:23:40Z","content":"It violates federal law.  I don't want children, and wouldn't wish unwanted children on anybody.  I'm pro-woman.  There are no good reasons in the world to be against this, really.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Corey Brehaut","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36023655"},{"created_at":"2014-03-17T22:32:34Z","content":"For woman's rights !","like_count":1,"author_name":"Julie Thompson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/60715682"},{"created_at":"2014-03-25T23:13:22Z","content":"It is a human right","like_count":1,"author_name":"Suzanne Clarke","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69773739"},{"created_at":"2014-03-19T17:44:56Z","content":"Everyone should have a choice.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Greg Stafford","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86589287"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:41:26Z","content":"Discrimination against women's health is an embarrassment to Canada.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Lindsay Hill","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/39998068"},{"created_at":"2014-03-18T00:53:17Z","content":"Every woman should be able to make the choice about what she wants to do with her body regardless of socioeconomic status and medical need","like_count":1,"author_name":"Jillian Farrar","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/51085128"},{"created_at":"2014-03-18T23:36:25Z","content":"I missed a chance to have an abortion at a young age.  I have regretted this for many years","like_count":1,"author_name":"Miriam Williams","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86516082"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T21:01:41Z","content":"Abortion is a personal decision and access should not be dictated by having the financial means to afford the procedure. Shame on the government of New Brunswick for not funding the services provided by the Morgentaler Clinic in Fredericton.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Hilary Ready","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/83435335"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T17:03:17Z","content":"There are many children in situations which no child should be in. If a woman cannot go though with a pregnancy she should not be judged but supported in this decision. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"lindsey colbourne","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85565511"},{"created_at":"2014-03-15T00:54:19Z","content":"The law needs to be upheld. Women deserve to make this difficult choice for themselves and they should be allowed to do so without having to jump through fiery judgmental hoops. How many young girls have gotten pregnant and because of an already difficult decision paired with a bad financial situation end up not getting the procedure they needed only to end up on social assistance? There is an unusually high percentage of single mothers on social assistance in this province and I'm not going to say that it is solely the fact that New Brunswick is not upholding it's laws but I feel it is fair to assume that there is in some capacity a correlation between the two. Now, just so I am clear about this I want to state that there is nothing wrong with being a single mother on social assistance; everyone needs a stepping stone and when you are young and pregnant and alone ( because some asshole skipped out on you and all his responsibilities) you do what you must. My point is this; the young girls and women who need this procedure the most are quite often the ones who cannot afford to pay for it out of pocket and because of this they end up paying for it for the rest of their lives. It should not be used as a form of birth control but I believe everyone deserves a second chance.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Jennifer Correia","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85787346"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T04:41:45Z","content":"10 out of 13 provinces and territories in Canada provide full or partial coverage of abortions in Canada. New Brunswick is not one of those 10. All Canadians deserve equal opportunities, especially when it  involves human rights sanctioned by Canada. \r\nWomen, whether they are teenagers or adults, deserve the right to choose whether they need to sacrifice their dreams and future for a child, while the male does not. Especially when they may be struggling with school payments or living payments and cannot afford an abortion, let alone a child. While adoption may be a wise choice in this situation, how could you ask a mother to abandon her child to someone else? By denying this service free, or partially free, of charge to all women, you are asking many women to do this, or give up their dreams to become a mother earlier than they would have planned.\r\nWhile pregnancy is a wonderful gift, a woman should be able to choose what path her life will take, no matter how much money she has. This is why I ask that you consider providing full funding or partial funding to abortion clinics in the province of New Brunswick.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Megan Penney","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85378881"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T18:01:58Z","content":"Many women in the world and in Canada stuggle with the decision to keep the baby, give it up for adoption, or to abort the pregnancy, and i think that is their civil right to choose, and in a way this is making some of the more poverty stricken women choose for themselves, because they can't afford however much they're asking. i will forever be pro choice.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Julia Bustin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/46369754"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T03:54:22Z","content":"Everyone deserves their own opinion and choices","like_count":1,"author_name":"Amanda Calhoun","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85376372"},{"created_at":"2014-03-23T12:32:13Z","content":"I believe abortion is a health issue and a woman's right to have a safe abortion funded by our government is a basic right ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Margaret Wall","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87041103"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T17:26:44Z","content":"The current situation is unjust for women in general, and even more so if you happen to be poor. I hope this petition succeeds. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Jose Ouimet","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85567821"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T16:54:03Z","content":"I trust women to make the right decisions for themselves and their bodies, and the current practices in New Brunswick are medieval and incredibly dated. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Joelle Badman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7369432"},{"created_at":"2014-03-18T14:17:36Z","content":"Women's choice ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Erin Bissonnette","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86446542"},{"created_at":"2014-03-22T17:18:44Z","content":"I believe that safe access to abortion services will save lives of women of all ages when confronted with difficult decisions. More healthcare options ensure better care. Lecturing at someone after a mistake is made doesn't fix anything. Providing a safe solution is the right approach.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Nicholas Cole","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/72535671"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T15:09:39Z","content":"Medical reasons only represent a portion of the many legitimate reasons to get an abortion. This  process is difficult enough without the extra barriers New Brunswick residents currently face. Please respect the Canada Health Act, which Health Canada has said mandates full funding of abortions at both clinics and hospitals.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Jessa Millar","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/jessamillar"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T23:48:24Z","content":"This is a massive, disgusting step backward in women's rights and the safety and health of us all. It's 2014. This is Canada. The NB government needs to get its act together and realize the closure of clinics like this does NOT mean that abortions will stop happening. It means they will stop happening SAFELY.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Grace Roche","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1667923"},{"created_at":"2014-03-18T01:38:57Z","content":"It's the law, bro!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Victoria Clow","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3129430"},{"created_at":"2014-03-18T00:10:40Z","content":"My body, my decision, period.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Deb MacNair","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86375533"},{"created_at":"2014-03-26T12:13:44Z","content":"Let's be fair, why should a woman in Alberta or BC have the right to a safe abortion paid for by Medicare, but if you live in Fredericton New Brunswick this service is available to you??? Do we live in the dark ages?","like_count":1,"author_name":"Patricia Galbraith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87413727"},{"created_at":"2014-03-14T00:10:46Z","content":"Bringing a child into this world is a choice, and must remain so, regardless of socioeconomic status.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Kelley Humphries","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85619166"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T10:13:43Z","content":"Women should be free to choose and finances should not dictate their choice. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Natasha Cormier","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85396256"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T15:57:48Z","content":"The Canadian Health Act should not be allowed to be ignored by New Brunswick.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Alisa Carnall","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8320522"},{"created_at":"2014-03-18T20:05:31Z","content":"Abortions should be funded in my opinion at both the hospitals and at the Morgentaler clinic.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Clare Gallagher","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56843242"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T01:24:04Z","content":"I am one of those 60% of NB women who was forced to pay out of pocket the total $850. It is a life choice every woman that they should be entitled to make. Lots of woman are forced to other options because this one has simply not been tangible for some time. It is a difficult process to see multiple doctors to sign off that it is \"medically required\" to receive one, as well as references to boot.  ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Caitlin Isaac","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85488353"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T17:44:27Z","content":"I paid out of my own pocket when I visited the Morgentaler Clinic.. it was worth it in so many other ways, but it REALLY set me back.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Ashley Briggs","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85442715"},{"created_at":"2014-03-18T20:56:44Z","content":"Not enough doctors will sign off so people can get abortions at the hospitals, and not everyone can afford to pay for an abortion themselves.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Johnathan Downing","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86499840"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T17:59:13Z","content":"women's choice is a right","like_count":1,"author_name":"Aeriol Liera","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85444319"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T23:44:49Z","content":"I believe it is every woman's right to decide what is right for her.  As a male, I have no right to take that away.  I also believe that all women deserve access to this service/procedure equally.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Anthony Burnett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85481866"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T03:02:21Z","content":"This is not just a women's rights but a human rights issue. We all have the right to equal access to quality care regardless of socioeconomic status or geographical location.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Sarah Colgan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85373173"},{"created_at":"2014-03-14T23:35:53Z","content":"It's a right to access to health care for all women who need this service","like_count":1,"author_name":"sandra devink","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7498377"},{"created_at":"2014-03-18T10:59:41Z","content":"Every Province in Canada needs to provide equal access to women's health services. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Darcie Lanthier","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10190433"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T14:10:26Z","content":"I believe it is a womans right to choose","like_count":1,"author_name":"Richard Russell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85547129"},{"created_at":"2014-03-27T20:54:55Z","content":"All women, regardless of socio-economic status, have the right to make decisions about their own bodies and these choices should not be limited by financial constraints or the political/religious beliefs of doctors.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Heather Tasker","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2667406"},{"created_at":"2014-03-18T15:16:27Z","content":"The woman's right to choose is a key freedom of the 21st century.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Trevor Morse","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/17127695"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T23:45:30Z","content":"Because every woman should have the choice and the ability to terminate their pregnancy for whatever reason. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Ruth Cox","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/70352456"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T22:22:19Z","content":"Because it's our damn choice! We shouldn't be slaves to our biology!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Katrina Kollar","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85474826"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T20:30:05Z","content":"It's time politicians openly support what they do privately.  This should be a standard in safe, responsive healthcare!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Ellen Wright","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85461457"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T17:41:29Z","content":"Timely access to abortion is a human rights issue. Women's reproductive rights are a building block of a fair, healthy society. Discriminating against women who need access to medical care is unjust and does not represent Canadian values.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Madeleine Bluteau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/84799747"},{"created_at":"2014-03-14T23:36:46Z","content":"Women deserve choices. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Laura Haley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85782516"},{"created_at":"2014-03-26T00:11:28Z","content":"Our province should be looking out for the best interests of it's current & future citizens. All women should have the right to a safe & timely choice, regardless of financial situation.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Stephane Leger","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87354838"},{"created_at":"2014-03-14T22:23:48Z","content":"I support women's right to safe healthcare and income shouldn't be a factor in that. I believe that the supreme court set a precedent for this healthcare in 1988 and New Brunswick women have been unfairly discriminated against monetarily in the ensuing years. As a native New Brunswicker I support the provincial government funding abortions at both hospitals and private clinic such as the Morgentaler clinic in Fredericton.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Alison Clack","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/63673673"},{"created_at":"2014-03-15T18:43:35Z","content":"There are far too many children being born into unhealthy situations. Abortion early in a pregnancy is acceptable in my opinion, and those who object clearly have no understanding of biology. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Whitney Sipprell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85903395"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T17:52:46Z","content":"I believe that women need to have access to safe, affordable reproductive options. Whatever those options are for those women and by closing the Morgentaler Clinic in New Brunswick you are severely limiting women's rights in New Brunswick and PEI. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kalie McIntosh","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7494002"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T00:24:56Z","content":"This is discriminatory, women's reproductive rights must be a priority  - if not now, when?","like_count":0,"author_name":"rowesa gordon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8330568"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T20:28:13Z","content":"Because without access, there is no right.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carole Aippersbach","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/883411"},{"created_at":"2014-04-19T18:32:58Z","content":"To not fund the Morgentaler clinic and simply let it disappear is an obstruction to women's rights and it is important to not stand idly by and let it happen.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Adam Stewart","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12605309"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T23:11:07Z","content":"Women need to have a choice and one they can afford without having to go outside the","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brigitte Martin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52812565"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T12:54:08Z","content":"As a mother, daughter, wife and friend I feel that every woman should have access and the right to the choices concerning her own body.  Her social and financial status should not be a factor.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jessica MacDonald","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89618297"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T17:43:27Z","content":"Once again, you are taking away women's rights","like_count":0,"author_name":"Valerie  Richardson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2028635"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T19:47:47Z","content":"We must support women's health!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jeremy Ewing","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7594473"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T21:02:15Z","content":"We deserve the right to our own bodies!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Elizabeth Teague","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32779495"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T21:23:32Z","content":"This issue is important to me because if I were to accidentally become pregnant I need to be able to have the right to an abortion. I don't want children and take the necessary precautions to avoid such a situation. Having a clinic like the Morgentaler in Fredericton gives me comfort knowing that there are options for myself and other women who may need it. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Emily Brown","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3624820"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T21:48:59Z","content":"As a native of New Brunswick, it is sad to see that it is still trapped in a mentality that should have disappeared long ago.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Paul Gomes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89290348"},{"created_at":"2014-04-02T21:43:46Z","content":"Government has no business being in a citizens bedroom.  Even less business to dictate what a woman's choice is for her body.  This is just another ploy of dictatorial control over New Brunswickers.","like_count":0,"author_name":"John Pettinen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87863019"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T22:46:10Z","content":"It should be important for the world.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amy English","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89299151"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T19:23:50Z","content":"Because access to safe abortions is paramount in female healthcare.  It is unacceptable for this clinic to close.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christopher Cook","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89651354"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T00:30:50Z","content":"Women are going to die because they will be forced to turn to unlicensed abortion providers who might prey on their vulnerability by charging extortionate rates for unsafe procedures. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christa Hudson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56007154"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T15:02:43Z","content":"Because they are LEGAL! Regardless of your opinion on pro-choice or pro-life,  abortions are a legal right and its absurd to make discriminate like this. Medically necessary or not its the woman's choice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christine Carr","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89248104"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:11:51Z","content":"L'acc\u00e8s \u00