 Wilson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89721915"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T00:58:54Z","content":"I believe all women should have a choice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Elizabeth Rowsell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89181460"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T22:27:28Z","content":"The women of New Brunswick deserve the right to govern their own bodies and to have access to safe abortions.  Save the Morgentaler Clinic and preserve those rights.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lena Duong","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31473728"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T22:46:13Z","content":"We, as women, should have the right to choose. The health and safety of our bodies is our choice.  End of story!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Deborah Canivet","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8205100"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T02:42:42Z","content":"Because as I woman I deserve rights to my own body","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Legge","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89424530"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T00:12:16Z","content":"This needs to change the government is wrong. Women should have this right","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mary Cronin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89310988"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T21:48:41Z","content":"Womens health and free choice.Not everyone wants to be a Mom for good reason","like_count":0,"author_name":"Joanne Nutter","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89787832"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T02:01:49Z","content":"Because abortion needs to be a choice that women are free to make.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ashley Wortman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89688246"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T13:24:19Z","content":"This is a service that is incredibly important for women's rights; lets move forward NB, not backwards. Women need to have access to SAFE abortions. Lets not force women to harm themselves to cause abortion in unsafe ways or contribute to the added spin-off costs that this lack of service will cause.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Emily Tompkins","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89364475"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T00:58:27Z","content":"We should have a choice and we should not have to get two doctors approvals to be able to make that decision. It should not be made more difficult. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gabrielle Michaud","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89497149"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T21:45:57Z","content":"Abortion is legal in Canada and all women deserve the right to decide what happens to their own bodies. To close the Morgantaler Clinic in NB will jeopardize the health and safety of girls and women, particularly the young and those who are economically disadvantaged. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Siobhan Murphy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/59376335"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T15:01:35Z","content":"Women's right to chose a pregnancy can't be a reality without access to safe and free abortion services everywhere in Canada.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lise Moisan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2161255"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T17:16:23Z","content":"women should have the option to choose and be provided safe care","like_count":0,"author_name":"Elaine Kenyon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89540037"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T04:05:47Z","content":"Everyone woman should have the right to access safe health interventions if they have to make this very difficult decision.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jaime Beaton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2606058"},{"created_at":"2014-03-23T20:43:53Z","content":"All women across Canada deserve access to government-funded, compassionate healthcare.   ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Justine Spencer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32723821"},{"created_at":"2014-03-20T00:42:28Z","content":"This is important to me because everyone deserves a choice. Who am I to say that a person cannot choose what they can do with their bodies. As a male I do not know the struggles women go through in making these decisions, but what I do know is that they deserve a voice and I cannot be a person who takes that away from them. How can a person honestly believe that a child would be better off in a world that it was forced into? Why ruin many peoples lives in exchange for a clump of cells that don't mean anything yet, it makes no sense to force people into decisions that they cannot even know the repercussions of.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Logan Murray","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86641003"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T10:55:54Z","content":"A woman has an absolute right over her own body. Anything less means her body is not her own. Unwanted children cost society far more than abortion services provided free of charge.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Allan Nelson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89717982"},{"created_at":"2014-04-16T15:54:27Z","content":"The Morgentaler Clinic in Fredericton is a crucial practice for promoting and protecting women's health in NB. Letting this clinic close is an affront to health equity.","like_count":0,"author_name":"alexandra blair","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/14110919"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T20:20:03Z","content":"Because reproductive choice is a fundamental right for women, and lack of safe access to abortion is criminal negligence on the part of NB government.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kyle Bridgett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89550829"},{"created_at":"2014-04-17T19:01:36Z","content":"Access to safe abortion is a woman's right","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sheila McIntyre","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34994165"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T13:16:54Z","content":"Everyone deserves equal access. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Peel","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47279306"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T13:24:24Z","content":"Many young folks are moving away, and this does not help! We need to save New Brunswick!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bonnie Huskins","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/59039476"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T01:05:45Z","content":"Because it is not right to tell women what they can and cannot do to their body. And the option to get an abortion should be made available to all women. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shannen Hemming","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89181986"},{"created_at":"2014-04-27T14:37:59Z","content":"As a woman, it is important for me to do my part in keeping a part of our freedom in New Brunswick.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sherilynn Gilbert","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9278018"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T18:27:53Z","content":"Women on PEI have had to use this clinic because they cannot obtain an abortion in their own province. Perhaps NB could get  PEI to help fund this clinic. It is time for women to have access to safe abortion if they so choose, no matter where they live in Canada.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amy Swenson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11537447"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T15:37:02Z","content":"Because it is a human right, and because I lived in the days before good abortion care was both legal and available. The NB govt is in contravention of the Supreme Court of Canada Decision and of the basic human rights of women in NB and PEI. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gayle MacDonald","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/61581484"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T04:05:51Z","content":"moving forward with the times... not backwards. freedom.... ","like_count":0,"author_name":"elissa king","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/23487538"},{"created_at":"2014-04-20T17:23:17Z","content":"This was put into law many years ago and the NB government has no right to be a law unto themselves.  Furthermore I lived through the time when abortion was illegal and saw first hand the suffering and even death that resulted and even then it was mainly poor women who suffered.  We should not have to re-fight this battle in this day and age.","like_count":0,"author_name":"laura tremblay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/75911033"},{"created_at":"2014-03-21T17:18:07Z","content":"Life.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rebecca Craig","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86847207"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T10:32:37Z","content":"Nobody should be able to dictate what someone else does with thier body","like_count":0,"author_name":"Steve Ramsay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55116768"},{"created_at":"2014-04-18T08:21:01Z","content":"Women should have the right to choose. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jessica Moyer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/90078876"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T19:12:32Z","content":"I'm originally from Saint John, NB, and it makes me angry that if I ever needed this service, that I wouldn't be able to get the help I needed.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amy Janes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10807517"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T16:11:11Z","content":"Freedom for women","like_count":0,"author_name":"Johanne Forget","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89745723"},{"created_at":"2014-03-24T13:22:33Z","content":"No one has the right to tell some one what to do with their own body. It is a personal choice....not a choice for others to make.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Audrey Hanselpacker","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52493921"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T19:07:05Z","content":"It is important for women to have a choice, whether or not I support abortion.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Wood","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89768217"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T21:26:07Z","content":"Justice for women..","like_count":0,"author_name":"John Calder","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89785878"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T00:41:03Z","content":"To give women a choice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hilary Kennedy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89683256"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T12:51:00Z","content":"We need to maintain a safe environment for women to seek medical care for their reproductive health and to maintain choice over their own reproduction and the direction that they wish for their lives to take. Women should have/need to have a choice over if/when they become a mother and not be forced to take matters into their own hands or be forced to seek help from unlicensed and unsafe \"practitioners\". NB needs to show that it cares about it's female population.  As women, we have a much different physiology than men and therefore, perhaps it is hard for male politicians to understand that this is a REQUIRED MEDICAL SERVICE for WOMEN. It's almost like saying labour and delivery services will no longer be available to women. How would that be okay? I am making a plea to the NB provincial and overall Federal government to step in and step up and provide funding for this essential service for WOMEN. \n\nSincerely,\n\nSarah Robinson","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Robinson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89361599"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T16:35:01Z","content":"While I advocate education and responsible living, I do believe that choice is paramount to our lives as \"free\" Canadians.\r\n\r\nWomen in New Brunswick should have access to the same services through Medicare as the rest of the country as a matter of principal.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Darryl Mullett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89381236"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T02:18:12Z","content":"Because choice is one of the things that sets humans and animals apart...And because we have a population crisis on our hands...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Andre Guimond","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12801233"},{"created_at":"2014-04-16T00:36:31Z","content":"Reproductive rights are human rights. People should have control over their bodies. Morgentaler is a Canadian hero. It's an awful shame that in his own country there are still places that don't recognize that we should be honouring that legacy, not shuttering it.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kevin Konnyu","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31034303"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T01:23:07Z","content":"Because I believe that abortion is a women's right to have and they shouldn't have to be charged for that right. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Whitney O'Kane","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28501417"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T22:47:30Z","content":"I'm a New Brunswick native (Edmundston) now finishing my residency in ObGyn at the University of Manitoba. I have seen both the positive and negative effect of accessible termination. I am also proud to say that I have provided these services in my residency and am planning to do so for the duration of my career. New Brunswick is not a third world country and needs to provide these services.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Deanne Malenfant","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89558488"},{"created_at":"2014-03-28T10:30:51Z","content":"Parce que c'est un cas de discrimination envers les femmes qui ont le droit de d\u00e9cider elles-m\u00eames d'avorter ou non, peut importe la raison de leur choix.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nicole Vendette","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/40997512"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T03:12:29Z","content":"Because I am a woman!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Beverly Jochems","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89587014"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T05:03:47Z","content":"The healthcare system is daunting enough for the average citizen.To put someone who is suffering through a traumatic experience under scrutiny and to burden them financially for making a decision that is obviously difficult and life-altering is an added duress. These decisions are not generally made lightly. I also  believe that unbiased counselling/therapy should be offered/given prior to and after any procedure.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Desiree Smith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89592979"},{"created_at":"2014-03-26T18:11:15Z","content":"For the respect of women right","like_count":0,"author_name":"Danielle B\u00e9dard","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87458885"},{"created_at":"2014-04-16T03:36:55Z","content":"Pro choice. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Virginia Redden","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69762831"},{"created_at":"2014-03-25T03:45:22Z","content":"Because every woman should have the rights to her own body, no matter the revenue she has...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Vanessa Forgues","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87227485"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T12:54:22Z","content":"Pro-Choice. Women should not have to jump through hoops for such a private matter.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ian Kilfoil","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89618327"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T13:08:46Z","content":"Because every woman has the right to control her body. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rebecka Tomasson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28527458"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T00:18:54Z","content":"Because it should be considered a basic ^(*@ing right.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Scott Olsen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22287698"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T21:34:38Z","content":"I cannot think of a reason that I would choose to abort, however, it is my right to choose. It is my body and neither church nor state has the right to decide what happens to it.. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kerry McGrath","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89670413"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T15:42:52Z","content":"Dont' want an abortion? Don't get one. Don't limit other peoples access to quality counselling and safe care. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michela Comparey","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36254345"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T19:32:12Z","content":"This is a human rights issue and affect the health and safety of all people, not only women.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Erin Bidlake","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89652669"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T19:29:02Z","content":"The citizens of this country should not need a petition for this subject (not issue as the word issue implies a need for debate, which there is not). This service is so obviously necessary not only as a fundamental human right but also for quality of life and more importantly, medical reasons. Not having access to this service will cause far more damage to society than eliminating it.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lindsay McCluskey","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3594042"},{"created_at":"2014-04-17T03:16:36Z","content":"All women in Canada should have a choice","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carol Austin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/68834168"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T16:21:14Z","content":"Every woman deserves the right to feel safe and make informed decisions about their own bodies. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Byrne","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85307057"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T02:37:04Z","content":"I feel like a women has the right to choose.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kelly  Wilson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/14114266"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T17:21:26Z","content":"As a woman who 'came of age' before abortion was a legal option, and as a former provider of abortion services, I understand how important it is for all women to have access to safe, legal, and affordable abortion care near where they live. Women become pregnant without intending to under all kinds of conditions and circumstances. Even 1 in 3 couples who practice other forms of birth control regularly, may find themselves facing unwanted pregnancies during their \"reproductive lives.\" I have even encountered women who did not believe in abortion who have decided on abortion as their only viable option at a particular time in their lives. Women must not be penalized for the fact of pregnancy under any circumstances. The government of New Brunswick must consider reproductive health, including abortion, to be the given right of every woman under its jurisdiction. It is the law of Canada, and federal transfer payments for health should be used to ensure this right. The government of New Brunswick owes this, and more to the women of New Brunswick.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carroll Godsman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36397131"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T20:17:52Z","content":"Because access to free abortion should be every woman's right.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Aimee Schmidt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35758955"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T01:19:01Z","content":"Because safe, accessible healthcare for women, including abortions and the right to choose.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Maegen Black","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3146914"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T00:43:00Z","content":"It's ludicrous that a nation that prides itself on its healthcare system willfully ignores the huge public health crisis this represents, particularly in light of all the evidence that restricted access to safe abortion services simply increases maternal morbidity and mortality, to say nothing of the negative psychological, emotional, and social impacts an unwanted pregnancy has.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dr. Maeghan Keddy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89418268"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T20:40:02Z","content":"All women should have choice!  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Susan Hunter","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89664086"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T20:35:50Z","content":"pro-choice","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brandon Hickey","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89780024"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T13:47:28Z","content":"I want my sisters in new Brunswick to have the same access to abortion services that women in Ontario do. I find it appalling that NB women need to be vetted  by two doctors to get \"medically required\" status to have an abortion in a hospital covered by Medicare. This violates the Morgantaler Supreme Court decision of 1988 which ruled these restrictions unconstitutional because they violate women's rights!! TThis needs to change and the NB govt. needs to fully fund abortions at the Morgantaler Clinic in Fredericton and repeal the provincial law restricting payment for abortion services. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"NataliaSome of Toronot's historical Shields","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/53093545"},{"created_at":"2014-04-16T00:48:07Z","content":"it is because i think that women should have the right to but not as a form of birth control it helps with the cut down of people trying to do it them self witch can lead to more deaths andwho in this world wants to be the one that has these womens blood on there hands i no i dont they need this it is a must.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Richard Mcintyre","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89801849"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T03:06:43Z","content":"All people deserve access to safe, affordable abortions.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Heather Donaghy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/71368912"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T14:56:46Z","content":"This is unlawful and inhumane. Women must be able to control their own bodies and not pay exorbitant fees to do so.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jessica Burrell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/44531565"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T11:06:58Z","content":"C'EST TR\u00c8S IMPORTANT D'AIDER LES FEMMES ET DE LEURS DONNER LE CHOIX.","like_count":0,"author_name":"FRANCOIS CHIASSON","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89610074"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T12:57:19Z","content":"Pregnancy happens by accident and if a woman or the couple feel that they cannot handle the responsibility of having a child then they should have the option to not have the baby.  This isn't the middle ages and we don't need to live like it is.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jeremy Good","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89618770"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T16:30:44Z","content":"Every baby born has the right to be absolutely treasured, an