 to close from lack of funding. The Canadian gov't does not believe that this  first clinic should be funded by the gov't. I sign the petition to help and please gov't of canada. Or anyone that will support.share. Go to site. I kno a lot of ppl that believe that they are killing lives. But its the one who has to live physically and mentally for the rest of their lives. And that child askn about their father. You wana be the one who slaps you child in the face an say\" ur dad. He raped me , that's how you came into this world. Im sorry if you take offence to this, but can you step in that child's shoes for that moment. I can't see some one being able to mentally deal wit that , i appreciated his clinic being there when i was in need. And was deeply saddened to have learnt he passed away. I was 24when this happened to me. At  26  i was pregnant again.and my beautiful 17 yr old is and was the right time in my life i was ready and she turned my life around but she was wanted \nI was mentally ready and her father may not b in our lives.but hes welcome to it, i am thankful that clinic was there when i needed them.nand better off now, if i had chose or if there was no one to do this for me. I dont think i could have carried to term and i could not have gone through with it. I would not be alive today if i had had the victim child,  don't kno if i said this right.but its my story and i am happy today and forever more;)","like_count":0,"author_name":"Natasha Buck","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89364008"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T17:47:47Z","content":"Respect our right to abortion.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jessie Brown","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78379750"},{"created_at":"2014-04-28T18:35:24Z","content":"Because it is an important health care which should be available to women","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jean-Guy Cormier","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32127465"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T16:36:41Z","content":" Without proper facilities, isn't there a greater risk of these women hurting or killing themselves to avoid unwanted pregnancies?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jon Beatteay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89748412"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T13:19:56Z","content":"People have the right to choose whether they want to keep their child. They should not have to fork out a fortune to do so, or travel to other provinces. Perhaps a young adult get pregnant and knows not only can they not afford to keep a child, but if they have to have the child it will put a strain on them and probably the social welfare system. What's more expensive, a one time thing, or 18 years of paying subsidies for a child?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Grainne McKenna","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/51128857"},{"created_at":"2014-04-28T16:44:25Z","content":"Reproductive Rights are basic Human Rights and NB is violating our Charter of Rights. I'm not coming to visit NB again as a tourist until this decision is repealed.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Joelle kolodny","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91018200"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T15:37:17Z","content":"Prochoice","like_count":0,"author_name":"bianca mallaley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/60818956"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T00:43:41Z","content":"Women are allowed this choice in Canada and it's important to keep it that way. Don't let N-B go without an abortion clinic.","like_count":0,"author_name":"marie levesque","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/46930548"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T02:43:48Z","content":"Everyone should sign it. I don't see a single reason why not to. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tyler Spriggs","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89424591"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T00:01:15Z","content":"protect  women, protect children, protect families","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ruth Canning","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/51915032"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T01:03:08Z","content":"As a woman I deserve all options available to me under the law.\n\nI am a Nurse Practitioner as well as a Sexual Assault Nurse Examiner and have referred several patients for services to the Moncton family planning and  Morgentaler clinic.  I count on these services to be available to my patients.  They deserve accessible judgement free services no matter what their circumstances.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alexis McGill","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89684594"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T12:42:43Z","content":"Because my daughter requried this procedure a number of years ago in Alberta, and it was readily available. It is a woman's body and she has a right to decide. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Deborah Everett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85410510"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:39:38Z","content":"This is 2014. Women should have access to an abortion clinic WITHIN every province!! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennifer Fowlow","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/62048096"},{"created_at":"2014-04-28T19:06:06Z","content":"As someone born in NB, I find the status quo unacceptable and in the dark ages.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Caroline Brown","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28990806"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T21:12:32Z","content":"L'acc\u00e8s libre et gratuit \u00e0 l'avortement pour toutes les femmes, au Canada comme partout dans le monde, est une question de droits humains et une condition pour une vie juste, hors des diktats conservateurs, patriarcaux, religieux, racistes, colonialistes, capacitistes et n\u00e9olib\u00e9raux.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sandrine Ricci","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/33649103"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T03:22:45Z","content":"It is very important to me that all women have equal access to reproductive choice, regardless of their income or their place of residence.   It is time for New Brunswick to act in the spirit of Canadian law, the Health Care Act and according to basic social justice. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jane  Doull","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29474937"},{"created_at":"2014-03-24T21:52:39Z","content":"Women's choice for abortion is very important for gender equality. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Charbonneau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87206338"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T08:40:45Z","content":"Because I had an abortion 2 years ago, and because of that have been able to carry on with my education. I believe that everyone should have a choice, and that without this clinic, there may be a girl who is unable to go to college or finish her education because of one mistake.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dani Lane","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89343260"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T15:43:17Z","content":"Funding for safe, free abortions should never be jeopardized unless the health of women just doesn't matter.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Simone Newstadt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15591925"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T06:43:55Z","content":"Because every government must follow the law. Because we settled this nearly three decades ago. Because the New Brunswick government is making it harder for Canadian women elsewhere to get safe and reasonable access to abortion.","like_count":0,"author_name":"HJ Hornbeck","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/62012436"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T11:53:38Z","content":"because it's 2014 and I cant believe this is still an issue.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Patrick Belzile","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89356824"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T16:09:32Z","content":"Because when I return from studying in another province, I do not wish my health care to decline based of legal actions that are no more than discriminatory practices against women.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rebecca Caissie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/65875039"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T18:46:30Z","content":"I am female and I should have the right to choose.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shannon Goodine","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89266408"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T16:24:33Z","content":"Women need to have the right to choose - I've been in this situation and was able to utilize it. I wouldn't do it again because I am now READY for it. But at the age of 20, and without the support of the father, I could have just kissed my life, my career and my dreams goodbye. Please don't take this right away from the women in this province. It's never an easy choice to make, it's something we have to live with forever. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Julie Roy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89380337"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T15:34:30Z","content":"Because it is not my choice to decide when it is right to bring a child into this chaotic world. It is the right of the mother and father to choose. If it is sincerely morally right to put a dog to sleep to avoid misery I believe the mother and father should have the choice on whether or not they can raise a child right at that time.","like_count":0,"author_name":"jeremy layton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3603879"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T03:56:07Z","content":"This is a medically necessary service for Canadian women. I don't want the era of women dying in back alleys from the inability to obtain a safe, legal abortion to come back.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Heather Wallace","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3167511"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T20:35:38Z","content":"Do not allow reproductive health to plunge back into the mid 1900s.  Follow federal law, and fund the Morgentaler Clinic!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Angela Day","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31826008"},{"created_at":"2014-04-27T16:25:01Z","content":"This closure will cause grave  inconvenience to the needs of women in distress forcing them to travel further to get care and perhaps cause great anxiety due to twitting times and appointments.","like_count":0,"author_name":" Joan Barrett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22053254"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T23:09:15Z","content":"Men can and do walk away from unwanted pregnancy. Sometimes men cause pregnancy forcibly and without consent. Women deserve the right to choose and a government willing to support that right. Stop taking steps backward and support the women of your province.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Erin Mackay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8129725"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T01:25:04Z","content":"It just is.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brian Winsor","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89316030"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T11:09:32Z","content":"We need to give women better financial and emotional support.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Valerie Paton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/64131498"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T15:50:12Z","content":"Women need choices!!!  This is not a privilege, It's a right","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kristen Olson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69716007"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T19:23:47Z","content":"all women should have a safe choice, not just those who can afford it.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Meghan Whyte","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/17188506"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T18:45:22Z","content":"Everyone should have a choice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ashley Johnston","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89392485"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T02:48:38Z","content":"Because I am an avid believer in women's rights and this is just not right. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Caroline Mallais","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89189824"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T15:12:15Z","content":"Abortion rights in Canada are far\r\nbetter than in the States, but this is only true as long as clinics\r\nremain open, and can provide safe options for women","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chantale Potie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8442960"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T21:50:45Z","content":"Supreme Court says access is a right. So Do it! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Liz Miller","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10789427"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T20:04:22Z","content":"Abortions won't stop; safe abortions will. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jena McLean","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89549949"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T21:34:22Z","content":"Human rights.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kris Powers","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2719318"},{"created_at":"2014-04-28T02:13:48Z","content":"I am shocked.  I had no idea that abortions were not paid for in NB, and that women are forced to jump through hoops to justify their need for an abortion.  I thought we were better than that in Canada.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chris Wilson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28225882"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T16:37:56Z","content":"What we do with our own bodies should be a basic right.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kim Macklin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/59122601"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T20:13:13Z","content":"Women need to be able to have the ability to choose their own future and control their own reproductive help. Any roadblocks to this (such as limiting access and availability) are attacks on women's right to choose.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sara Stredulinsky","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89399847"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T22:05:59Z","content":"Accessible abortions raise the quality of health of all the atlantic provinces. It is a basic right to be able to make choices concerning our own lives and bodies and should be maintained.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Anna Taylor","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8130288"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T02:23:54Z","content":"Women across Canada deserve access to full reproductive health care, and in fact should be guaranteed it under Canada's human rights laws.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cara Gibbons","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35333557"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T02:05:26Z","content":"Everyone in every situation has the right to decide what they want for their body, and for their future.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jessica McCormick","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85369087"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T14:48:53Z","content":"Women shouldn't have to jump through unnecessary hurdles to exercise their rights. These rights shouldn't be up for debate. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Caitlin Kimmet","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/25776528"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T14:44:24Z","content":"A woman's right to choose what happens with her body is not something that should be watched over by our government. We are people too!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tracy Molyneaux","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1684979"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T11:59:16Z","content":"People should have the right to choose","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jeannot Thibodeau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9227932"},{"created_at":"2014-03-17T20:06:22Z","content":"People need to be able to access services from as many qualified providers as possible. If they pass inspection I do not see why any clinic would not be allowed to perform this procedure.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kent Scanlan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78064150"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T19:19:15Z","content":"women need access to safe abortion facilities in order to save lives. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jessica Slipp","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12128880"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T21:02:46Z","content":"I feel very unsafe and disgusted that so many people do not see how important having a safe, healthy, clean, free abortion clinic is.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Vanessa Russell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89284145"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T20:40:29Z","content":"Women deserve to have all opotions for their reproductive health available to them, including abortion services. It is not right that women in New Brunswick are expected to pay out-of-pocket for this health service if they choose not to have it performed in a hospital setting. And then certainly should not need two doctors providing a written note that an abortion is \"medically required\". What a waste of health care dollars to take up the doctor's time for that when abortions are provided by health professionals already.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Calinda Brown","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/21064723"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T21:03:14Z","content":"Constitutionally protected rights take precedent  over petty politics that only serve to reinforce discriminatory practices.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jeremy Doucet","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85214040"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T19:15:13Z","content":"I feel every women should have the option if to whether she should be able to keep her baby or not.","like_count":0,"author_name":"TIna Murray","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89649989"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T22:44:56Z","content":"Women should have the right to choose! The fact that we are still dealing with this kind of thing today makes me so angry I can't see straight.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Molly Leeco","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78354192"},{"created_at":"2014-04-19T17:09:00Z","content":"Because I know people that have needed and used this service.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Beth Hagerman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35813980"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T17:54:55Z","content":"What a sad state of affairs! New Brunswick and Prince Edward Island are two of the only provinces left in which provincial health care does not pay for the procedure, unless deemed medically necessary. This puts women in an unfair situation without the safe options that Canadian women living in other provinces have. If the issue is really about money, this may be a controversial standpoint, but I think it would probably be cheaper to fund terminations through Medicare than to fund income assistance, not to mention the other expenses that come with the growing population, for people who continue to have unplanned children. This is an example of political opinions overriding\r\nwomen's rights, and it is fucking outrageous!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennifer Bovard","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11886358"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T19:02:23Z","content":"Access to safe and affordable abortion clinics is extremely important. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Anna Allossery","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89393974"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T21:46:38Z","content":"Because I believe women have the right to control their own reproductive health.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Laura Stephenson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85219191"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T23:20:11Z","content":"I believe all women should have the right to choose.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Elizabeth O'Keefe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89305896"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T18:37:00Z","content":"Abortion is a legal and safe service that everyone deserves access to. No one should be stopped from exercising their civil and reproductive rights by matters of distance, finance, and other people's ideologies. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Elaine Tamblyn-Watts","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3236248"},{"created_at":"2014-03-14T14:38:27Z","content":"The right for ALL women to have a CHOICE and for ALL women in Canada to have universal access to SAFE medical abortions in a CARING environment.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Melanie Presby","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85696249"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T21:18:09Z","content":"The power to choose ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Heather Goodine","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89669124"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T01:03:30Z","content":"Because women should have access to health services for procedures that have been legally protected in this country for over 25 years, and failure to fund them is a violation of our charter rights.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alex Dezan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89684617"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T02:02:40Z","content":"For the health of women all over the Atlantic Provinces.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Claire Prideaux","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28638481"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T10:31:24Z","content":"There is nothing sadder than an unwanted baby.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Liz Demerson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89350621"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T18:46:33Z","content":"WOMEN'S RIGHTS TO THEIR OWN BODIES NEED TO BE RECOGNIZED","like_count":0,"author_name":"Robyn Dean","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/40895743"},{"created_at":"2014-05-05T16:44:38Z","content":"I'm a transplanted New Brunswicker and I'm ashamed at the state of women's reproductive rights there","like_count":0,"author_name":"Matthew MacLean","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22016091"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T16:41:44Z","content":"I have used these services and would have been in a very difficult life situation without these services being accessible.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Crystal Noddin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89630773"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T20:37:53Z","content":"As a young person graduating this year, starting my career in New Brunswick this May this issue is very important to me.  I take pride in living in Canada, a progressive country.  Unfortunately New Brunswick seems to continually lag behind and this is yet another example.  I am looking forward to building my life in the maritimes and want to be part of the solution.  I know government is doing it's best to move the province forward, and this is an issue which if ignored will be a huge regression for New Brunswick.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Benjamin Buckley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89401829"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T15:45:44Z","content":"Women should have the right and resources to get an abortion. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Wentzloff","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89534566"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T23:00:03Z","content":"I agree that abortion is intrinsically important, but when I was in my child-bearing years and single, if raped, I would have wanted an abortion nevertheless.  I feel all woman ought to be able to have access to an abortion in sich a case.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Janet E. Watts","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/60912372"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T20:46:05Z","content":"woman have the right to good health care","like_count":0,"author_name":"john houston","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89664578"},{"created_at":"2014-03-26T14:20:34Z","content":"All women's rights issues are human rights issues, and their resolution is necessary. This is an issue I was only recently exposed to and I was previously unaware of the inaccessibility of abortions in my own province. I would like to support this cause in any way that i can! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carolyne Mellon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87427479"},{"created_at":"2014-03-24T06:45:33Z","content":"because my body is my right!","like_count":0,"author_name":"marine hardy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16067135"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T12:51:33Z","content":"Parce que le droit d'avoir un avortement appartiens \u00e0 la femme m\u00eame ..... personne d'aurte.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Diane Daigle","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89617961"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:54:13Z","content":"Because I am pro choise and always will be.  SCIENCE.","like_count":0,"author_name":"amanda fillier","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89377830"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T16:09:40Z","content":"It is important for women's reproductive rights to be honoured, respected, and be ultimately prioritized by our provinces and country. Those considering abortion should not have to worry about costs and accessibility of the procedure.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennifer  Anderson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10127055"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T16:40:29Z","content":"Because people should be able to make their own decisions on their life.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Geneva Delarosbil","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/83986464"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T19:11:39Z","content":"Because women should have options and it goes against our rights as women. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Emma Dufresne","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78388108"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T23:13:18Z","content":"Women in New Brunswick absolutely need this. We need safe, medical abortions. We are the only province that does not stand behind the needs of its women when it comes to family planning. It is as simple as that. There are a lot of major issues in this province that we can begin to resolve with the funding of these services. We are far behind the rest of Canada. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Holly Savage","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89304527"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T23:20:12Z","content":"It's important that women have access to a basic right to choose what to do with their own bodies, without it having to be deemed \"medically necessary\" or paying money they may not have out of pocket.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Paige Guy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3343188"}]}
