urent","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/40429764"},{"created_at":"2014-03-26T23:55:24Z","content":"Abortion services are a matter of health and equality for women","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ginette Bastien","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87501740"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T19:09:22Z","content":"Not every woman has the resources to parent a child in the way  that they deserve. Let women be in charge of their bodies and make choices.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hailey King","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85197637"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T19:49:05Z","content":"My free choice","like_count":0,"author_name":"Danielle Harrison","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89397874"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T16:15:31Z","content":"Libert\u00e9 de choix des femmes","like_count":0,"author_name":"Pierre Bellefleur","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89746158"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T02:44:23Z","content":"Women in NB should have the same right(like other women across Canada) to access to abortion facilities since abortion is legal in this country and not have to endure these unfair burdens put upon them by the NB government.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Corey MacDonald","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/57367877"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T23:07:50Z","content":"Because there is no reason that anyone should be able to make a decision about my body, other  than me. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Quinn Schofield","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47122262"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T00:33:05Z","content":"Every woman has the right to choice and control over her body.  Period.  End of discussion.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jane McLean","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85362080"},{"created_at":"2014-03-24T20:25:38Z","content":"Abortion must be free and accessible for every woman","like_count":0,"author_name":"Genevi\u00e8ve Albert","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87196894"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T11:59:23Z","content":"Women need access to safe options. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Natalie Fraser","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47106618"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T15:33:31Z","content":"People should have the right to choose and in certain situations like rape or incest it is the best solution, do you know if this clinic closes does it mean people in Fredericton can't have abortions? Or just that they need to go somewhere else, ie. another clinic or the Hospital? If not it's down right cruel to get rid of this service.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carolyn Guy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89251349"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T12:46:30Z","content":"It is important for any women to have the right to choose. If this service is taken away women will have to resort to scary and dangerous means. What is the women or teenager has no insurance to cover birth control, what is they were 13 years old, what if they were raped?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Samantha Jones","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/21034730"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T16:32:06Z","content":"Every woman should have the right to choose.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kayla Gallagher","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89256054"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:59:37Z","content":"this is important to the young woman who need the choice.  Men should not have any say in the matter.  Life is not life until it can sustain itself.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Karen Goodwin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2571344"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T17:01:32Z","content":"Women should have the right to choose - without funding for this clinic, that right is non-existent.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gregory Toole","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89383450"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T19:54:44Z","content":"The right to choose should not only be extended to those who have money.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sonny Nauss","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86833852"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T03:46:01Z","content":"Because every woman needs to be given an opportunity to decide for herself, not be forced into a situation because of financial stress. You never know what someone's situation is and should never assume it. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Felicity Barry","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34565200"},{"created_at":"2014-04-16T01:30:39Z","content":"each and everyone's situation is different, and you deserve the right to make the decision...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marlene Chase","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89806013"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T04:21:09Z","content":"everybody should be able to have the choice","like_count":0,"author_name":"Katherine Puskas","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52702723"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T16:47:46Z","content":"Women are denied equal medical access across Canada by sexual discrimination. Honour womens human rights under the Charter now!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nancy Niles","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13074361"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T10:17:10Z","content":"Human rights should be important to everyone. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Pamela Austin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89349631"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T22:18:19Z","content":"Women deserve the right to choice in all aspects of their lives. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"clay cutting","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30897672"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T00:03:19Z","content":"A woman;s right to have control of her body.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda Cameron","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89494929"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T16:19:08Z","content":"Parce que les femmes ont le droit de choisir. Parce que mon corps n'est pas une question politique. Parce que pas avoir acc\u00e8s au avortements, ca pose des probl\u00e8mes a la soci\u00e9t\u00e9.  Je soutiends d'ailleurs que ce devrait \u00eatre un service gratuit et accessible. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Natalie Belliveau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89379915"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T17:32:38Z","content":"Abortions are a human right and should not be restricted","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marion Arthur","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/44466229"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T21:49:30Z","content":"The closure undermines women's right to reproductive rights in my home province.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ryan McNeil","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/84790181"},{"created_at":"2014-04-16T15:20:20Z","content":"Fair access to abortion services and a mother's *choice* in the matter are both legal in Canada. The provincial government has absolutely no business restricting that access or denying choice through unnecessary regulation. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ian McLeod","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58231516"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T00:44:11Z","content":"Women should have the right to choose","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dawn Vincent-Dixon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89418344"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T17:09:39Z","content":"Access to abortion without needing consent from physicians is the law of Canada. New Brunswick continues to break this law by requiring that women get written medical approval for this procedure from two doctors.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jacqueline Low","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/59111295"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T06:56:45Z","content":"Funding the clinic in Fredericton is important to me because I recognize a woman's right to choose, and I recognize that abortion service in NB hospitals is effectively denied to many women on account of the two-doctor signing-off rule. It is also important to me because I know first hand how the religious right creates fear in those who recognize a woman's  right to choose and her right to access to safe abortion service.     ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hal L","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89597099"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T14:49:28Z","content":"Women's rights. As a woman who has had an abortion at a young age and wouldn't have been able to pay.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Verity Stevenson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47181694"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T14:00:58Z","content":"Human beings should not be treated like brood mares.","like_count":0,"author_name":"David Mitchell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/33652387"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T19:42:06Z","content":"My partner is from Moncton, where we met, and we often think of moving back to New Brunswick to be closer to his family and the Acadian culture. Unfortunately, it is a lack of progressive attitudes in the province that keep us from coming back. Women's rights are important!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Naomi Burkhart","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/76617618"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T17:03:02Z","content":"I'm pro-choice, and this means making choices accessible to all who need them. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christie Dennison","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85311962"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T01:38:05Z","content":"My Mother stood for a woman's right to be freed of male strictures on her body. I have always supported this.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Thomas Barnes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/65232678"},{"created_at":"2014-03-27T13:38:33Z","content":"Sovereignty over our own bodies as women. The right to choose belong to us and us alone. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Emily Lockhart","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34183227"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T13:41:23Z","content":"Poor women need to be able to access abortions rather than having more children on the welfare system.","like_count":0,"author_name":"beverly brett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24715080"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T01:21:24Z","content":"Women's rights. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Autumn Locke","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85488178"},{"created_at":"2014-04-16T01:51:03Z","content":" Its a huge part of womens rights. There are many reasons why a woman chooses to have an abortion. Our province should have a safe place for women in need to go. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alana Scott","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6351668"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T17:15:31Z","content":"I grew up in New Brunswick and left in 1997. I have not had any desire to return, what with its gradual decline back into the dark ages. The closing of the Morgentaler clinic inclines me to believe I made the right choice, and that this decline is at this point irreversible. \r\n\r\nStop treating not-yet-viable fetuses as more important than the real, fully-realized human beings on whose vital organs these fetuses depend. Women have the right to CHOOSE to be pregnant, not to be forced to share their organs with another merely-potential-human at someone else's whim.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jason Thibeault","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9656018"},{"created_at":"2014-03-14T22:33:50Z","content":"MY BODY IS NOBODY'S BODY BUT MINE! As in I make the decisions that concern my body and health, no one else! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Katie Rasmussen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85776550"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T15:53:52Z","content":"Access to safe abortion is paramount to maintaining a high standard of health care for women in this country. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Elizabeth Burtt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8448568"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T23:16:31Z","content":"safety, free-choice, free access. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ryan Gallant","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89413134"},{"created_at":"2014-03-19T22:20:05Z","content":"Women's right to choose should not be linked to her financial means.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mike Price","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11801148"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T01:25:18Z","content":"This is a choice that should lie in the pregnant women's hands alone. No government policy, and no person, should prohibit a pregnant woman from having this choice. Really glad to not be in N.B and now I will put visiting the province at the bottom of my bucket list, purely to show my lack of support for this choice. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ashley Stewart","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89316053"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T03:09:23Z","content":"Because I am a woman.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michelle MacGillivray","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89322982"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:03:09Z","content":"Without this clinic I would have not had access to a safe abortion procedure. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michelle Lavoie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/77410979"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T12:28:09Z","content":"All women deserve to have control over their own bodies, whether one believes in terminating birth or not. The option should be available and SAFE. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christina Coffey","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89727217"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T19:20:37Z","content":"Women should have the right to decide. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Anna van Nostrand","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/63881095"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T15:40:42Z","content":"NB women need and are entitled to this option!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Renee Motty","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89624473"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T18:20:22Z","content":"To promote universal access to reproductive choice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"janice gorodzinsky","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85189596"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T18:27:36Z","content":"women should ALWAYS have a choice","like_count":0,"author_name":"Victoria Coulson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89390986"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T00:31:56Z","content":"As an adoptee I feel qualified to say that a woman's reproductive rights should only be determined by her with the help of her physician. Inequality comes in many forms. Medicare was designed to combat societal inequality, and elevate the status of women and children. Having lived in New Brunswick for over a decade, as a single, intelligent woman with a high school education, even with some work-provided medical coverage, an unexpected pregnancy would have taken food from my mouth and from my rent. I was fortunate in that my only unexpected pregnancy ended in a miscarriage, which cost me nothing. Don't misunderstand me. The experience was a sad and painful period. I mourned the child and felt tremendous loss. However, at the time, I was practicing safe sex with the use of birth control. I did not want children. It's incredibly sad and I am disappointed to know that I was lucky because my body made a decision for me that I, otherwise, would not have had the financial ability, nor the basic human right to make. Particularly when 50% of the human population can choose to walk away from a situation like this at any time, yet still earn more money than I can. This is not equality, New Brunswick. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amanda Rogers","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56117665"},{"created_at":"2014-03-26T12:31:54Z","content":"Every child should be born cherished and longed for!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Vicky Leger","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87415932"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T00:32:43Z","content":"As a man this particularly doesn't effect me however I believe these services should be widely available for women. We fund so much waste in this world, I don't understand why we can't fund something that can prevent the ruin of more than one life. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Corey Miller","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/82950315"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T16:58:23Z","content":"So long as abortions are not free and accessible by choice, our society is inequitable for women. This is a right and we should it have to continue to fight for it again and again.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Eleanor King","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8130881"},{"created