"http://api.change.org/u/89260381"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T12:53:04Z","content":"All women should have access to quality health care of their choice. Do not remove the right to self determination for NB women.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dianne McCormack","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89729856"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T21:52:43Z","content":"because i have had one from this clinic and a lot of different people may need them rape/ defect birth control/ accident etc","like_count":0,"author_name":"stephanie lebrun","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89290891"},{"created_at":"2014-03-24T14:57:48Z","content":"Every woman needs access to safe, affordable and accessible abortions.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Laura Mikuska","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87161032"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T23:46:34Z","content":"Why is access to abortion codified in the Canada Health Act if it is so flagrantly disregarded??? For shame. New Brunswick women deserve as much choice as women in British Columbia, Alberta, or Ontario. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Renata Gordon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/77888376"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T19:05:17Z","content":"I'm from New Brunswick originally, and every single woman, there or anywhere, deserves access to health care, including abortion.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Becca McLeod","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15087254"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T15:25:20Z","content":"Access to abortion in 2002 was so important to the wonderful life I've had ever since. Can't imagine not having such freedom. It's outrageous.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kerry Clare","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89250560"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:21:48Z","content":"Every woman has a choice. Every woman has a right . An option for a safe medical procedure should not be compromised based on \"society's opinions\". ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennifer Pade","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2473181"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T19:56:37Z","content":"Get with the times, NB is one of 2 provinces that does not fund this necessary procedure. People will die without it. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jason robin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89549474"},{"created_at":"2014-03-14T23:19:35Z","content":"I am pro choice","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carol Morrison","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85781036"},{"created_at":"2014-03-24T11:57:12Z","content":"denial of this funding is unjust and illegal","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chris Kaposy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87141822"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T21:15:11Z","content":"ALL woman have the right to have an abortion if they choose no matter their financial income.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Julie Lurette","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89404663"},{"created_at":"2014-03-28T00:46:21Z","content":"Women are not incubators! We need to have control over our bodies so we can choose to have children when it is right for us.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Susan O'Donnell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87651331"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T00:19:30Z","content":"We have allowed our government to ignore a supreme court ruling and forced women to rely on a private clinic and pay out of pocket for too long. Now even that option is gone. It's barbaric and against the majority of Canadians values. We, as a province, should be ashamed. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Danie Pitre","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89311497"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T00:12:27Z","content":"There is a steady backlash going on towards women's services. This is deeply regressive and disturbing .","like_count":0,"author_name":"Debbie Lifshen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/68869728"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T20:53:18Z","content":"women need access to clinics ","like_count":0,"author_name":"katie holmes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52903951"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T16:54:52Z","content":"this is non-negociable, people need this access, and if they don't it puts their lives in danger.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Zivi Richard","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89257758"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T17:42:23Z","content":"previous NB resident, this is a blatant move against pro choice","like_count":0,"author_name":"Julian Teakle","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89637700"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T00:24:36Z","content":"Because we shouldn't even be debating this.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Katie Avery","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89178954"},{"created_at":"2014-03-24T15:26:33Z","content":"Parce que la d\u00e9cision des femmes \u00e0 mener une grossesse \u00e0 terme leur revient de plein droit.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sylvie Pinsonneault","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87163851"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T18:06:00Z","content":"I believe, with all my heart, that women need access to safe abortion.  I believe that the women who most need this access are the financially disadvantaged.  I believe that access should not depend on how rich you are...not in Canada.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Susan Spence","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/77356398"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T00:13:41Z","content":"It should be the womans right to choose whether or not she wants to do this, the supreme court already struck down this law as unconstituitional ages ago, is NB stuck in the dark ages?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Al Mason","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58321280"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T12:53:34Z","content":"Because it is a choice woman should have.  A personal choice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tracy Flowers","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55437974"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T11:59:30Z","content":"New-Brunswick can't afford to take some steps back when it comes to Womens' rights. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tyler Durden","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66995571"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T15:11:09Z","content":"This should be important to all Canadian Women!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Katya Duhamel","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3267257"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T19:17:13Z","content":"Women should have a right to choose without legal or financial barriers.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kim Ferguson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89269711"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T17:55:17Z","content":"As a New Brunswicker living in Ontario, I support NB (and all) women's right to equal access to fundamental reproductive health services. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stephanie Ross","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2065541"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T18:45:53Z","content":"I don't think that women should be treated as second-class citizens. This means that women should have the option of accessing all the services required to live healthy, happy, productive lives. I feel that access to safe abortion is one of these rights. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Matthew Cole","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85193588"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T22:46:43Z","content":"For the hope of progress. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kevyn Mackeigan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24896249"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T20:09:07Z","content":"Overpopulation, food shortages and the ever increasing climate changes make for a rather uncertain future for any child. I strongly believe that anyone should have the right to choose what happens to their bodies. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Robin Carson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89659191"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T20:16:59Z","content":"Women need the right to safe care and determine their own needs. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Allan Patrick","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/5125305"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T20:04:46Z","content":"A woman should't have to go through all the \"red tape\" of obtaining authorization from 2 physicians to get an abortion, which she might not even get anyway. She should have the right to chose. This should be paid for by Medicare.I already have to pay for healthcare for people who chose to smoke and have health related conditions, or for people who have type 2 diabetes, which could be controlled by nutrition but instead, people are opting to take medication instead of changing their life habits.  Some pro-life will say aborting is killing, but the law is clear on this, the unborn child is not a child. Also, state and religion should remain separate. Politicians should do what is right, not what will determine their faith in the next election.","like_count":0,"author_name":"St\u00e9phanie LeBlanc-McIntyre","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89549972"},{"created_at":"2014-03-24T18:32:53Z","content":"I have a right to publicly funded medical treatment no matter where I am in Canada. Requiring abortions to be done only in hospitals is an unfair hardship imposed for non-medical reasons.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michelle Noel","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3574066"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T02:16:05Z","content":"It's not a question of why, it's a question of why not. Why wouldn't you support a woman's rights to her own body?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chelsea Grigg","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85242134"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T02:18:34Z","content":"New Brunswick women should have as much right to choose what happens to their bodies as all other Canadians.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stacey Narrowmore","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/49381808"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T15:08:15Z","content":"Women have a right to have control over their bodies. This has already been decided by the courts and the people. The government needs to stop making decisions based on perceived issues to serve their narrow party interests and start making decisions based on actual issues that affect the people of Canada.","like_count":0,"author_name":"John Alexander Jenkins","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89462809"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T09:34:50Z","content":"Because women have the right to choose!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Katie Gillis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89712107"},{"created_at":"2014-05-05T14:43:28Z","content":"Making something inaccessible is akin to making it illegal, which it's not!  The hypocrisy must end.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mireille Albert","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22957535"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T13:33:11Z","content":"The question is not if \"I\" am for or against abortion as a personal choice.  The importance is that the women have choices and can make the decision on their own.  Nobody else should be able to make the decision for the women and their should be no obstacles before them if they do chose abortion.  Not having choices is discrimination against women.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jos\u00e9e LeBouthillier","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89733859"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T14:12:51Z","content":"The government should be enabling the people to make educated and responsible choices to resolve mistakes they may have made even if they were irresponsible mistakes. If we want children to have good healthy lives then we  need to allow those who feel they are not ready to bare children make that decision. Freedom of choice is also freedom to be able to make that choice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alex Harvey","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22854733"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T21:51:15Z","content":"Woman's rights are worth fighting for.","like_count":0,"author_name":"James Crump","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/59977311"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T15:12:57Z","content":"There is a serious lack of access to abortion services on the east coast of Canada. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kelsey Yarlett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/53356472"},{"created_at":"2014-03-18T21:51:22Z","content":"Reproductive rights are basic human rights that must be upheld by a modern democratic society. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nikolay Afonin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86506351"},{"created_at":"2014-03-24T19:25:54Z","content":"Remember, \"if men got pregnant abortion would be a sacrament.\" Steinem\r\nTime to use it again.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sonja Greckol","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9671496"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T23:28:08Z","content":"On behalf of women and the underprivileged everywhere...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Leslie Stompor","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89678632"},{"created_at":"2014-03-23T23:28:09Z","content":"Les femmes ont le droit de faire ce choix sans avoir besoin de l'approbation d'une tierce personne","like_count":0,"author_name":"marie-noel ross","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87098769"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T18:13:22Z","content":"What's the point of giving us \"options\" when you take them away from us? This is wrong and they know it. I think it's sick and disgusting that we have to be forced into a choice by the government and regardless of what you believe on this topic, you should believe in the freedom of choice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennifer Gerard","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6771321"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T12:51:54Z","content":"I lived nearly a decade in Fredericton and so issues like this are of High concern to me. 1. The laws of needing two doctors to sign the ok for having an abortion (fail)\r\n2. An abortion needing to be termed Medically necessary (fail) and yes if it is medically necessary sure do it in hospitals. but for those exercising rights on their bodies - they should have access too.\r\n3. Morgentaler is the only clinic for ALL of NB - also PEI doesn't have a clinic either.\r\n\r\nfor those who are prolife - the clinic staying open doesnt change a thing about their right to decide to be pro life.\r\n\r\nBut the clinic closing extremely hinders the right for pro-choice people to exercise their right to make a choice.\r\n\r\nTHAT IS THE FUNDAMENTAL ISSUE.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennifer Chiasson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89361682"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T11:44:18Z","content":"It is a woman's right to control her sexuality and her pregnancies.  Birth control systems are not 100% effective.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Donna Kasdan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47543849"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T22:45:17Z","content":"For those who dont have any other options","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stephane Doucet","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89491597"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T18:30:37Z","content":"Women deserve to have the right to abortions! Simple!! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sandy Nicholson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89265066"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T20:47:58Z","content":"Women's reproductive rights! Safe and legal access to abortion for anyone who wants it! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jovana Jankovic","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34070796"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T17:50:25Z","content":"Because it will suck","like_count":0,"author_name":"Robyn Caldwell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89425344"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T21:43:42Z","content":"Because Women are important to me.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jake Winters","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89406724"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T23:02:41Z","content":"Keep the clinic open. The government thinks they can't afford to keep it open but if that is the case they probably can't afford the extra subsidies,  people on welfare, child services and everything else that goes along with it that will result from people not having an accessible option available. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jillian Girouard","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89302466"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T19:44:25Z","content":"Because it's the right thing to do! Freedom of choice is as important as every other freedom we enjoy here in Canada!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Andr\u00