thor_name":"Sarah Winchester","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78453129"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T00:44:39Z","content":"Because abortion is a right!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Catherine Flores","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29904904"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T19:32:38Z","content":"Repeal 84-20....it's the law!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mary Nelson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89652751"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T11:41:44Z","content":"I'm from Moncton, and to see my home province try to get away with this is shameful.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Harrison Makohoniuk","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3588270"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T04:09:06Z","content":"Coat hangers, bleach in uteri, pelvic pus, perforated uteri, disfigurement, sterilization, and death.\r\n\r\nAll in the name of your barbaric moral code.\r\n\r\nKeep funding the clinic, or prepare to bear the responsibility for the aftermath.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ben Harries","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9751603"},{"created_at":"2014-03-23T22:32:50Z","content":"Women deserve the right to choose; our bodies are not the property of a church.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Margaret McLennon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87095034"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T02:43:13Z","content":"I'm heavily pro-choice and don't think someone should be forced to carry a baby they aren't ready for or if they were raped. A baby is better off not born than brought into a world unwanted.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Megan Gallant","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/51139541"},{"created_at":"2014-04-26T17:57:47Z","content":"As a physician doing my residency training in the Maritimes, I am appalled at the barriers women face for reproductive health services.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brodie Marshall","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/90880649"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:35:44Z","content":"Parce que l'acc\u00e8s \u00e0 l'avortement est un service essentiel pour les femmes du Nouveau-Brunswick.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Catherine Arseneault","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/60788288"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T15:38:19Z","content":"Everyone who needs access to safe and secure medical procedures should have it.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Wendy Gross","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/393675"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T21:38:29Z","content":"Because women deserve to choose.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Erin Lapp","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16016399"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T00:39:58Z","content":"Everyone should have access to abortion services!","like_count":0,"author_name":"camille O'Sullivan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/84326578"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T17:15:55Z","content":"Because deciding to have an abortion is a woman's basic right over her body.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jill Lewis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89471318"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T18:28:04Z","content":"Women need access to this service in NB. We need to move forward instead of continuing to take steps backwards. This clinic cannot operate without the support of the Government. We are one of the only Canadian provinces that doesn't give women the right of choice. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shawn Boyle","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89391016"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T16:34:59Z","content":"Access to safe abortions is a right for all Canadian women.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alice Burdick","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/4982951"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T19:49:24Z","content":"Why should woman's rights disappear? Men can receive a vasectomy without reason; however, females can't have a hysterectomy without reason. Expect an increase in self-harm and suicide, as well an increase of money into welfare, social assistance, family allowance and child tax - if the clinic is not funded!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Colbi Flanagan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/76100350"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T02:18:10Z","content":"This is a NEEDED service for ALL women who might need it!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mary Burtt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89423289"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T00:07:55Z","content":"Women should have the right to choose. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Wanda Moulaisson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89310657"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T20:34:20Z","content":"Although I would not choose this option for myself, I cannot condone removing the choice from others who may do so. Doing so privately helps protect them from discrimination and prejudice and funding it helps protect women who are in a vulnerable group.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rene Legacy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37518124"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T00:14:50Z","content":"eem","like_count":0,"author_name":"Peter McComb","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11163327"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T20:21:51Z","content":"I am a woman","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cyndi Robinson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89550928"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T01:27:51Z","content":"I believe in every woman's fundamental right to make decisions about her body. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jill Morris","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45085214"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T12:29:33Z","content":"women's rights. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brittany MacKenzie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/50194343"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T16:19:39Z","content":"Reproductive rights are human rights that shouldn't be up for debate. Funding for this healthcare is essential and imperative. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Megan Couture","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/41699281"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T18:00:01Z","content":"Choice is a human right.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jessica Xie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89262498"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T19:02:52Z","content":"In the medical field and appalled the frankly anti-woman policies of the NB governments surrounding abortion over the past 20 years. Come on Mr. Alward, give us a reason to believe in you. We need change now, not election promises.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jason Retallick","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89394007"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T18:16:30Z","content":"As a woman who has lived most of her life in NB, this issue affects me personally and deeply. No woman should be forced to give up her rights; no government should be allow to strip her of them.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Faye Simmonds","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89642475"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T16:40:50Z","content":"Everyone should have the right to decide what they should do with their own body in a safe environment.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Erin Fischer-Fox","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89537786"},{"created_at":"2014-03-29T05:48:08Z","content":"Having lived in NB, and attended STU I fully support these students endeavours to make health care equal and accessible. It is always fascinating when pro-lifers fail to acknowledge their tax dollars in action for children born from unwanted pregnancies. This may include services such as tax credits, welfare, and/or foster care. If money is your primary motivation to deny access I suggest you start re-calculating your choice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christine Smith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/54255335"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T20:25:49Z","content":"I had a therapeutic abortion in June of 2010, and I often wonder how different my life would be if I had not had this option. 4 years later, I have a happy 16 month old with a KNOWN and present father, and I believe any woman should have the choice. The choice should at least be available to make.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Samantha Krinis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/50456597"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T21:10:28Z","content":"As aphysician I know how important it is for women to have prompt access to abortion if that is their choice. I have seen what denial of service leads to.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Johannes van Spingelen MD","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/20907652"},{"created_at":"2014-03-23T21:06:12Z","content":"Because New Brunswickers deserve accessibility to these services.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gabrielle Ross-Marquette","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3582383"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T14:50:56Z","content":"Many will die and many will have their suffering expanded. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"James Riesberry","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/83361534"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T20:46:18Z","content":"Abortions save women's lives!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Melissa Brooks","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/72223967"},{"created_at":"2014-04-26T23:25:56Z","content":"I need access to abortion. The economy is bad enough in new brunswick without a new generation of unwanted children being jobless, birth controls have fail rates, and some people do not have access/can afford it. politicians need to stay out of my business. Men of an older generation should have no say over what happens in this generations ovaries!","like_count":0,"author_name":"meghan taylor","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6747113"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:40:04Z","content":"avoir l'option et l'acc\u00e8s est essentiel aux droits de la femme","like_count":0,"author_name":"maryse arseneault","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/64651033"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T18:42:50Z","content":"As a woman and a mother of three daughters, this is part of essential Medical services in NB.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennifer Griffin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89266072"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T01:00:38Z","content":"I'm a woman, and I should be able to make my own choices.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Erika LeClair","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89181595"},{"created_at":"2014-03-24T14:26:53Z","conten