/89818678"},{"created_at":"2014-04-17T07:12:37Z","content":"COME OUT OF THE DARK AGES, GOVERNMENT OF NEW BRUNSWICK! Stop violating Canadian law that allows women free access to abortion. The Morgantaler Clinic is keeping women from dying from botched abortions, not to mentiont that you are denying women choice over their own bodies. Disgusting!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sera  Baker","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24883541"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T19:14:11Z","content":"It is important that women have access to this type of health care service because it is no longer 1752. Since women have the legal right to abortion, they should ACTUALLY HAVE it. Imagine any other right to a health care service being offered, such as the right to get an X-ray under regular health benefits, but then having to get two doctors to refer you (especially in a region that is short on doctors), pay for the service yourself, and possibly have to travel long distances to access the service, which increases the cost even more. It's ridiculous! But for some reason, it's okay to do this when it comes to services relating to women's bodies. It's time that women not just have their formal rights recognized by the Courts, but they need substantive rights recognized in health care funding and practices. I'm so disappointed in the NB government.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Allison Hines","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47072930"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T19:24:46Z","content":"I believe that women's reproductive rights should be considered a priority to the government of New Brunswick. Therefore, I believe that the government should fund services at the Morgentaler Clinic in Fredericton, NB.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Emilie Bourque","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24158611"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T18:41:00Z","content":"Women's rights to reproductive health must be maintained","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christine Smith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8964