e policy.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda Kealey","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/19858583"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T16:54:39Z","content":"Pro choice ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Katie Gormley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78388291"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T15:08:26Z","content":"Because everyone should have the right to choose! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jessica Hughes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89620899"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T07:25:20Z","content":"EQUALITY.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Leanne Przybylowski","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89509556"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T20:35:54Z","content":"it clearly violates the supreme court decision, its not right that we keep losing our rights.","like_count":0,"author_name":"amanda mallet","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55965719"},{"created_at":"2014-04-17T19:21:27Z","content":"We live in Canada in 2014. This should not even be up for discussion anymore. This is a massive blow and a huge disappointment in every aspect and for every person faced with unwanted or unprepared pregnancy. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hannah Rice","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/90027346"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T23:08:56Z","content":"Choice is important, access to health care is a Canadian right. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"christine bilinski","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89793237"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T01:21:06Z","content":"Women should always have a choice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Donald Baird","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85365694"},{"created_at":"2014-03-13T03:17:49Z","content":"There should be a choice of having an abortion in a hospital setting or a clinical setting. Hospital administered TA services are always more expensive than the same serve done in a free-standing clinic.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jeannette Bergunder","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85495015"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T15:11:24Z","content":"We are moving backwards in time. Women should have the right to decide what they do with their bodies. This is saddening!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Danielle Smith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3575545"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T23:06:28Z","content":"This is important because every woman should have the choice to keep or end their pregnancy. It also should not cost 700-800$ to do it. It is a medical procedure, therefore should be covered by canadian medicare. Yes, ending a pregnancy may not have anything to do with the woman's health, but it could be because of a personal choice, economic standing, or other, and that choice should not cost the person a lot of money. Give government funding to abortion clinics in canada. Even if the patient needs to pay 50$ as an appointment fee, thats more reasonable than 700-800$!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ashley Linden","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22400465"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T21:36:39Z","content":"La libet\u00e9 de choisir pour chaque femme.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ginette Duguay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/88040830"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T11:32:55Z","content":"It is a woman's decision & right, not one made or taken on a whim! This province is going backwards and I fear the butcher shops will open up again! Shame on this province!\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"Arlana Parker","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89448839"},{"created_at":"2014-04-16T00:00:05Z","content":"Women have every right to choose. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Andr\u00e9a Cameron","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89797854"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:17:48Z","content":"Medical assistance should be available and affordable for all.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Samantha Lee","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89374637"},{"created_at":"2014-05-05T16:27:13Z","content":"It seems unbelievable to me that in 2014 New Brunswick would be violating a right given to women by the Supreme Court in 1988.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Clarice Ondrack","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/42253944"},{"created_at":"2014-05-06T18:53:28Z","content":"access=choice. NB is putting women's lives in danger by restricting their rights. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stefanie Brantner","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91797510"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T18:13:04Z","content":"Because reproductive rights are human rights ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Megan Sexton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85319115"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T23:32:29Z","content":"The health and rights of women is far too important to disregard. This represents a massive step back, more clinics should be opening rather than closing the only accessible clinics for two provinces.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Adam Dias","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/44533687"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T19:14:25Z","content":"Because choice is important.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christian Steenhorst-Baker","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6942845"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T03:52:18Z","content":"Everyone deserves the right to help, especially safe help. If this clinic closes down there is very few other locations to have abortions in NB so many women will be facing little options.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sabrina Smtih","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/39037718"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T05:17:32Z","content":"It is a women's right to her personal autonomy and security to have access to abortion services and they should be provided by our national health care system - it is simply a necessary service. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"mary annis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10703743"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T16:20:03Z","content":"Because Canada's abortion laws were shown to be UNCONSTITUTIONAL in 1988. Why is accessibility still such a large problem? This is infringing on a woman's right to chose. Come on people! It's 2014!!!!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alison Williams","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89379969"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T13:57:22Z","content":"This is not about pro choice or pro life, this is about having safe, medical care options for women. History has shown us that out-lawing abortion or inadequate access to clinics like this, is detrimental to the community. This current provincial government has an extreme amount of shortfalls, but women's health should not be part of a political agenda. This is a no-brainer whether you are pro-choice or pro-life, the access needs to be available and woman need to have the option for safe care if this difficult choice is laid before them. This is about woman's rights, and it pains me to know that the closing of this clinic is even being considered. It's a sad day for any woman living in this province, knowing that her rights are not a priority.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alexandra Pascon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1423065"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T21:25:06Z","content":"NOT OK.","like_count":0,"author_name":"MIRANDA PROSSER","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89287218"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T00:11:08Z","content":"I am a woman, and I have rights!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hillary LeBlanc","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3569836"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T00:55:41Z","content":"This is a human rights issue and the fact we have to go to this length is ridiculous!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Drew Carleton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89314074"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T07:40:20Z","content":"The premier's religious beliefs have trumped a constitutional right of women and contravened laws. Men MUST stop dictating women's reproductive rights. We are now in the 21st Century. Having our lives run and ruined by men is a thing of the past or should be.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nancy Crouse","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7608095"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T00:36:00Z","content":"Get with it New Brunswick, obey the laws of Canada","like_count":0,"author_name":"Peggy   Woolsey","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/19880356"},{"created_at":"2014-05-29T11:35:36Z","content":"All women should have the right to choose whether they want to keep the baby or not. For a country that claims that we have a right to freedom & we have freedom of choice, this goes against our own statement. If we are already paying taxes, then we shouldn't have to pay for an abortion","like_count":0,"author_name":"Natalie Landry","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/102641215"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T19:43:45Z","content":"Women should have the freedom to do what they want with their bodies. Abortions are important to the health of women.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nicole Barry","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89397425"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T20:38:40Z","content":"Women should have equal access to medical care across Canada.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Abbie Garvey","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7547222"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T22:58:11Z","content":"Coat hanger vs. professional doctor, people will do what they want, might as well be safe.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stanley Petley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89301642"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T16:48:33Z","content":"Because women's reproductive choices have been under fire for too long and because NB's requirement that two doctors approve a woman's abortion is in direct violation of the system the SCC ruled was unconstitutional in R v Morgentaler.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Eva Lane","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89538319"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T18:08:33Z","content":"I no longer live in New Brunswick and I likely will never go back. The province has NOTHING for me anymore. I couldn't even get a job in fast food, which I'm overly educated for in the first place. Now with this New Brunswick has proven to be more backwards than some third world countries. I'm actually nearly ashamed to say that I grew up here because of this. And the government wonders why there is a \"brain drain\"? Because we are sick of their lack of brain and we cannot take the drain it causes anymore.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amanda Wardle","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89263189"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T12:36:31Z","content":"My family is from New Brunswick and my grandmother, aunt and cousins still live in Fredricton. I want my cousins to have the same access to health services I do.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Edan Thomas","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/50716213"},{"created_at":"2014-04-16T18:26:25Z","content":"Because I think it is important to have a choice that is not dictated by their financial situation. Morgentaler has helped countless women and it is important it continues to do so; and not only in metropolitan areas. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Madison Ala","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52787604"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T01:45:29Z","content":"Medical treatments must not be restricted to the rich. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kathy Dawson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31092868"},{"created_at":"2014-03-26T14:18:37Z","content":"Everyone deserves to have control of their own body. If the government has decided to fund these procedures, I don't think they should make it so hard to access.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rebecca Stewart","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/73177164"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T03:10:42Z","content":"Because women need to have the right to do what they want with their bodies. It is their choice. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"V\u00e9ronique Poirier","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89323052"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T19:08:52Z","content":"This is important to be as I believe that women have the right, their human right, to make their own decisions based on what is best for them. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jamie Thomas","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89478427"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:08:47Z","content":"I support a woman's right to choose","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jenna MacPhail","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89373861"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T18:23:02Z","content":"c'est important pour que chaque enfant qui vient au monde le soit parce qu'il est bel et bien d\u00e9sir\u00e9 par ses parents","like_count":0,"author_name":"Charbonneau Manon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89264439"},{"created_at":"2014-04-21T19:27:13Z","content":"women's rights of choice is being removed or given to a medical process","like_count":0,"author_name":"robert ferland","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/90326491"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T16:12:22Z","content":"Women have a right to choose what happens to their own bodies and they have the right to have access to proper health care, regardless of their financial situation.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Lockyer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2583395"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T18:38:12Z","content":"This is important to me because I believe that women should not be denied their reproductive rights.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Anita Nathan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89544852"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T23:35:16Z","content":"I think it is very important that all women in Canada and elsewhere have access to safe abortions","like_count":0,"author_name":"Phyllis Fischer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/54133892"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T04:32:08Z","content":"This is a \"women's issue\" and due to the stigma my hopes that services will be funded are not too high, but that does not make this any less important. This issue is not just a women's issue. It is a human rights issue. Without this clinic, the government is allowing the belief that a man can choose to leave an unwanted pregnancy and a woman can not. Without this clinic, abortions will still happen but in very unsafe, and often fatal ways. Consider the weight your choice to ignore this issue will cost the lives of women living in and around New Brunswick who need this. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Angela Brown","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22637557"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T01:32:53Z","content":"Abortion is between a woman and her doctor. Also, come on. This is Canada, not the uber-religious United States. What a person does with their body is nobody's damn business. Also? This won't stop abortions from happening. This will just make it a hell of a lot more dangerous. Congrats, BC, you just jumped back about 100 years in terms of women's rights and healthcare.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nakita Gibson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/76187001"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T22:03:13Z","content":"because women's health is everybody's issue. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"adele flannery","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/21104602"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T17:40:36Z","content":"Choice is a woman's right. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Angie Arsenault","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8204223"},{"created_at":"2014-03-09T19:48:18Z","content":"I believe that women's reproductive rights should be considered a priority to the government of New Brunswick. Therefore, I believe that the government should fund services at the Morgentaler Clinic in Fredericton, NB.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Allison Mee","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85097356"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T03:58:33Z","content":"I am appalled that New Brunswick women have been suffering under these inhumane conditions for the 25 years that we in Manitoba have had access to abortions paid under Medicare as all necessary health services should be.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ellen KRUGER","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89428078"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T14:46:33Z","content":"The current regulation discriminates women of lower socio-economic status, and especially women who are victims of sexual assault.\r\nA better government would at least consider that abortion, being an important part of women's health, should be something that is covered by their tax paying dollars and not from their own pockets. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alice Shen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89246232"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T12:58:22Z","content":"Women should have the choice of what should happen to them.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sandra Deveau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89362206"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T12:24:58Z","content":"Access to abortion is a fundamental feature of equality and security of the person for women.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Natasha Bakht","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16969424"},{"created_at":"2014-03-20T11:55:07Z","content":"Because I am a woman and I have daughters ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carol Mousek","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86688938"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T17:22:50Z","content":"This is not the dark ages. We have made so much progress in women's rights, why take a step back on this one?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kristiana Croft","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/46972929"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T03:58:01Z","content":"Because Canadian women are lucky enough to have the chance to choose abortion and closing this clinic takes away that right for not one, but TWO, provinces. It's criminal, sad, and just plain wrong.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Leslie Ross","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89503332"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T17:45:10Z","content":"This is important to me because woman should be able to have a voice and obviously the NB government is trying to suppress that voice. Whether woman are having an abortion to simply not have a child, or whether its because they need to for a medical reason, woman should be able to make that decision. Shutting this down is just another example of how woman are treated lesser than men in today's society and that sickens me. Canada as a whole likes to talk about equality, yet the government and i