r_url":"http://api.change.org/u/92516344"},{"created_at":"2014-05-05T16:03:28Z","content":"The rights of women are indicative of an equal, fair and just society.  That these issues still need be fought is extremely disturbing. Peoples personal beliefs should NOT effect OUR rights","like_count":0,"author_name":"Vicky Edwards","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/39099296"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T16:05:21Z","content":"women deserve reasonable access","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gary Bridgett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87989460"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T20:48:23Z","content":"Access to abortion services is essential to the autonomy, health, and equality of all women. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nancy Janovicek","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58798178"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T17:51:25Z","content":"All women in Canada are entitled to accessible reproductive care of their choice. Canada needs to enforce the Health Act and fund the Morgentaler Clinic.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Laura Buechler","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9738138"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T20:42:12Z","content":"I'm a teenage girl.. self explanatory.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alyssa Comeau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/74601785"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T01:22:43Z","content":"I'd prefer to keep that to myself. I know there is no one to start a debate, but it is important and thats all that should matter. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jesseb O'Donnell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89420456"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T14:54:39Z","content":"Because women deserve a choice better than a back alley abortion \"clinic\"","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dave Rigley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89372607"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T11:35:07Z","content":"The New Brunswick Government has been allowed to discriminate against women for too long. It's time to catch up with the times.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Allison Brewer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1858587"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:18:01Z","content":"Parce que l'acc\u00e8s \u00e0 l'avortement est un service essentiel aux femmes du N.-B.!","like_count":0,"author_name":"M\u00e9lissa Thibodeau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3567414"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T17:06:24Z","content":"As a born NB hoping to move back someday, I think we need to get our laws up to the rest of the country and stop burying our heads in the sand.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shannon Myers","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55996436"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T18:01:48Z","content":"The existing statute does not allow for a right to choose. It should.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Richard Bennett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/44241529"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T23:52:08Z","content":"Women should not have their rights taken away, again. What year is this again??? Get with the times NB. ffs. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"chris pritchett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8320176"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T01:20:24Z","content":"The closure of this clinic as a result of non-funding will lead women who are not in a position to have a child to desperate measures that will affect their health and possibly lives. If a woman wants to terminate a pregnancy, we have seen again and again that she will do so, regardless of whether or not it is done safely..It is absolutely outdated and unfounded that our government thinks the system for obtaining abortions in a hospital setting are enough as they are limited only to women who want to have abortions for medical reasons. Therefore it completely ignores healthy pregnant women who have been sexually assaulted/abused/coerced, as well as those who have limited access to sex education or birth control. Furthermore, how can our provincial government justify being the only province not to fund a private abortion clinic. They have provided ABSOLUTELY no explanation for this and no justification for the decision not to fund the Morgentaler Clinic. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ilisha French","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3591419"},{"created_at":"2014-04-20T19:15:19Z","content":"It is extremely important for women's rights in Canada! We need to be the leaders for other nations to follow suit!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Allison Graham","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/90249504"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T01:58:34Z","content":"I am a former employee of this clinic an am now a midwife in Ontario because NB doesn't offer that choice to women. I support women's reproductive choices and abortion care is an important part of reproductive care. It is not optional: it needs to be accessible and safe. This is an essential service. Please respect the independence of women and the needs of women and their families and keep this NB abortion clinic open.\r\nIn my career future, I plan to take training through IPAS to become an abortion provider so that I can provide abortions in developing countries. I hate to think that women in the Maritimes will soon feel many of the challenges to access that people living under dictatorships, war and totalitarian regimes experience.  Shame!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carolyn Moffatt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89318323"},{"created_at":"2014-03-24T20:44:30Z","content":"Always women, not governments or doctors, should have a choice about their lives, their futures and their bodies.","like_count":0,"author_name":"maggie thomas","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2303980"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T14:06:33Z","content":"#NBPROCHOICE","like_count":0,"author_name":"Megan Mellanby","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/44400989"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T12:38:46Z","content":"I have had friends use their services.  that needed them. and it was the best decision for her and her family","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kristy Grant","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47116658"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T13:10:40Z","content":"this should be a basic human right","like_count":0,"author_name":"Margaret MacKenzie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89731575"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T17:28:23Z","content":"Women's basic rights. Everyone deserves a choice. SAFETY should be a priority. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Renee Belliveau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89385771"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T16:35:34Z","content":"I went to St. Thomas University for four years and was a part of loved ones' need to access safe abortion. I believe strongly in a woman's right to choose whether or not she wishes to follow through with a pregnancy and certainly feel that defining \"need\" by medical terms only is incredibly dated and excessively offensive to what rights we do hold in the Maritimes. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jenna Barnes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/14100454"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T17:24:09Z","content":"The right to choose is a human right that is upheld elsewhere in Canada, and an option that has come to the rescue of several of my friends. I think the clinic needs to be financed as a show of support for women in this province more generally.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shauna Chase","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89635028"},{"created_at":"2014-03-17T21:56:05Z","content":"Because I support women's rights to choose.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dave MacDonnell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86354208"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T17:32:24Z","content":"I personally believe that everyone should be entitled to a choice. Medical reasons should not be the only reason. Chances are they are not only doing it for themselves, but for the baby as well. If they know they cannot care for the child they are having, and they cannot have an abortion, the child is the one to suffer. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michaela Barton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89754855"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T18:52:58Z","content":"The closure of this clinic, together with the actions of the provincial government, effectively deny women access to the full range of reproductive health care services to which they are entitled.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Doris Buss","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89545701"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T14:54:40Z","content":"On May 16, 2013 I attended a rally for the \u201cPro-Choice\u201d side. \r\nWe lined up around the clinic (front & sides) with signs and did a silent protest as nearly 200 \u201cAnti-Choice\u201d people walked by with their signs, glaring at us. It was so intense! Some \u201cAnti-Choice\u201d people had signs that read \"Choose Life\" and \"Abortion is Murder\" ...glad to see they recognize that it is in fact a CHOICE! Not to mention, abortions are legal so making the CHOICE to have one is not murder, since murder is a punishable criminal offence.\r\n\r\nIt's time to change the way we talk about this issue. It shouldn't be \"Pro-Life versus Pro-Choice\" anymore. The conversation should focus on the already legal procedure remaining legal and more accessible to keep women safe and healthy.\r\n\r\nLET\u2019S BEGIN...\r\nI think people don't understand what \u201cPro-Choice\u201d means. \u201cPro-Choice\u201d is not a synonym for \u201cPro-Abortion\u201d; those are two entirely different things. \u201cPro-Choice\u201d simply means that you believe in a human being having the CHOICE, the OPTION, to seek a medical professional for an abortion; having the CHOICE to put their child up for adoption; or having the CHOICE to keep the child. It is all about CHOICES. Each person will CHOOSE what to believe in, whom and what to support, and will CHOOSE to pass judgment and make decisions for those whose lives and CHOICES we will not understand. I think that this is a very dangerous mistake and unfortunately it will hurt New Brunswick in the long term.\r\n\r\nI do not agree with the use of abortion as a form of birth control; however, what another woman chooses to do with her body is none of my business. I will not tell her that she cannot make the CHOICE to terminate the pregnancy just the same as she will not tell me that I cannot CHOOSE to carry to term. From one woman to another my responsibility is to support her in the CHOICE she makes, because it is her right to make that CHOICE and I will not try to take it from her. I think that women need to stand up for this service, even if they don\u2019t believe in abortions. (Sounds crazy, I know!) But this closure affects all women, even those who will never have an abortion and those who cannot conceive. That said, however, it is not just a women\u2019s issue; women everywhere need support from male counterparts on this issue.\r\n\r\nMaking the decision to have an abortion (to terminate a pregnancy) takes a lot of thought; she must weigh out pros and cons and consider her options before the decision is made. I think people assume that a woman who has an abortion must have found it easy to make that CHOICE, but in reality, the woman does suffer from it. She undergoes physical and mental trauma and many often seek counseling to deal with the emotional turmoil they experience.\r\n\r\nHaving the CHOICE to seek a medical professional for an abortion should remain legal and accessible to keep women healthy and safe. Women, throughout time, have managed to find ways and means of having abortions, and keeping it a legal, available, and safe procedure will keep many women alive. \r\n\r\nFrankly, if the province's Dept. of Education would start teaching Sexual Education rather than attempting to promote \"Abstinence Only\", young teens, and other aged women, might not have unexpected pregnancies. Not to mention, I think birth control (contraceptives, condoms, etc) should be FREE so that each person has access to it, and with that, the number of unplanned pregnancies would decline. I really do believe that better Sex. Ed and accessible methods of birth control will help as the number of women who seek the aid of a professional to perform an abortion will decline. While this is an incredibly controversial and sensitive topic, most people are not thinking of every possible situation, or the consequences of their actions and thought processes, and those inactions of the province of New Brunswick. Don't be too closed minded, folks! Challenge the province! Fight back! It is the only way that things will improve!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michelle Wight","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89372608"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T15:05:41Z","content":"Because in Canada womem have the right to choose.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kendall Lively","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89620513"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T14:19:56Z","content":"All Canadian women deserve the same medical care that I am able to receive as an Ontarian.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Allye Vice","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11652694"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T19:26:29Z","content":"Because I am pro-choice! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Emily Utter","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58977915"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T20:57:09Z","content":"Regardless of my personal opinions on abortion, I know there needs to be a safe, non-judgmental place for women who are in trouble to go for help.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alana P.","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/26686078"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T03:45:22Z","content":"This is taking away a womans rightS, what if she was sexually assaulted? Pregnancy is not always the woman's fault, were just the ones forced to carry it for 9 months. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Julie Ringuette","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55039998"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T02:43:45Z","content":"Had an abortion when I was fifteen and if I wouldn't have had one i wouldn't have been able to end up where I am today, graduated collage and working in alberta. I would have ended up on welfare like the rest of girls in New Brunswick. Thank god for that clinic. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Meghan O'Neil","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/77411032"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T15:26:32Z","content":"I'm originally from New Brunswick, and I'm ashamed of my home province for their unfair treatment of women. Shame on the provincial politicians who are not fighting this.","like_count":0,"author_name":"M\u00e9lanie Daigle","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3579653"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T00:05:31Z","content":"This is a matter of legal rights for women not religious opinions.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gary Waite","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/20002273"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T17:22:33Z","content":"Because this is an important cause !","like_count":0,"author_name":"Koichi Sato","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85181957"},{"created_at":"2014-05-05T21:23:54Z","content":"Women know when a pregnancy is wanted - let them make the decision, supported by our medical system.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Louise Carberry","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91712786"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T01:30:50Z","content":"It is a woman's right to control how her body is used. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ann Pohl","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28463662"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T15:32:47Z","content":"Dear Minister:\r\n\r\nAccess to reproductive choice is a hard-fought legal right of women in\r\nCanada. Your province's restrictive policies put the health and safety of\r\nwomen in New Brunswick at great risk. I urge your government to repeal\r\nRegulation 84-20 and to fund the Morgentaler Clinic which provides the much\r\nneeded service and care that your government doesn't.\r\n\r\nShame on you and your colleagues for reneging on your responsibility to the\r\ncitizens of your province. Cheryl Macaulay, Ontario","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cheryl Macaulay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89464329"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T12:09:45Z","content":"Essential to women's equality.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Virginia Gahagan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85279858"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T14:54:40Z","content":"Because women have a right to autonomy over their bodies.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Catherine Lapointe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89372611"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T12:13:29Z","content":"Abortion needs to be fully funded at the Morgentaler Clinic.  Why would we continue to restrict access to medical service that provides real choice for women of our province?\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"Loree Kaye","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89614783"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T16:41:26Z","content":"As a mother of a young daughter, the idea of her growing up in a region wherein her ability to one day access her rights is actively infringed upon disgusts me. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Caroline Craig","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89381782"},{"created_at":"2014-03-17T21:51:34Z","content":"It is a legal right in this country  and our provincial government should not create barriers for women who need this service .","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda & Harry Eisenhauer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78776271"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T17:45:39Z","content":"a basic, legal right is being denied to the women of this province and i don't support any government that allows this injustice to continue.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Taylor Seely","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89638105"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T22:56:44Z","content":"Seriously?  What is WRONGwith these guys?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shawn Dalton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89411766"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T22:56:25Z","content":"Women should have the right to determine what happens to their bodies. Politicians and religious zealots don't have the right to control women's bodies.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rachel Watters","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8135743"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T13:49:38Z","content":"I believe that women deserve and should have the right to choose what is best for them. Having access to safe abortions enables women to make safer, better informed decisions. Without access to safe abortions, women who may want to terminate their pregnancy may turn to dangerous means such as illegal \"back alley\" abortions or take the matter into their own hands, further risking their lives. Access to publicly-funded, safe abortions ensure the safety and overall well-being of our society's women - our friends, cousins, sisters, aunts, mothers, and the many other women we encounter in our lives. These women deserve our support and respect - not condemnation.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Adele Carrier","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89458154"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T09:23:26Z","content":"Because women have a right to adequate access for health care without cost,  and the Canada Health Act mandates coverage at recognized clinics.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hallett Llewellyn","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/17287521"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T17:25:10Z","content":"Because I believe that women's rights are being violated and that needs to change.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carolyn MacDonald","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/23433543"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T15:25:45Z","content":"Respect the right to choose, for all women","like_count":0,"author_name":"Robin Vose","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/38614039"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T14:03:09Z","content":"Women should have the right to their reproductive health. That right should be universal in Canada. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Frank  WIshart","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8212072"},{"created_at":"2014-03-20T15:46:50Z","content":"It's a breach of the human rights of women. This is something available in other parts of the country, and it should be available to New Brunswick women as well. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kristen Bullock","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86718941"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T03:05:32Z","content":"I believe all Canadians have the right to equal health care free from judgement. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shawnda Behrns","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89425628"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T00:50:18Z","content":"I support women's health. I support women's rights and freedoms. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Katie Loughery","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89313723"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T03:17:55Z","content":"girls should have the choice whether they want to have a baby or not and taking this away is taking away their right to that.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sam Gibson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89323515"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T14:39:47Z","content":"Everyone deserves an acessable abortion facility. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sydnee Dalton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/79949404"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T21:16:55Z","content":"this is a really important service we cant lose.","like_count":0,"author_name":"jordan gibson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89487007"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T00:53:12Z","content":"men should not be making decisions for women's bodies.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Laura Dawe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8144087"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T15:25:53Z","content":"A woman's choices and decisions regarding her reproductive health should be nobody's business but her own. The government of New Brunswick should be ashamed that they are stripping people of their rights and making essential services harder to access. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Natasha Arbeau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89622665"},{"created_at":"2014-03-20T12:39:36Z","content":"Womens rights","like_count":0,"author_name":"Matthew Chiasson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86693831"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T23:40:48Z","content":"It's a legal medical procedure, not a ideological decision by government.  I am asking for federal and provincial support for the Morgentaler Clinic in Fredericton, NB. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"The Edelsons The Edelsons","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/62422879"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T23:47:13Z","content":"Because every woman deserves the right to have a choice and to have access.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Emily Robinson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89309133"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T20:56:35Z","content":"Women should have the right to decide freely and with full accessibility if they want to carry a fetus. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Susan Jardine","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/38680107"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T02:24:09Z","content":"Women's basic Human Rights are non-negotiable!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Martha Solomon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13731560"},{"created_at":"2014-04-20T14:46:21Z","content":"Because I want the right to choose what I do with my body.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kara Maxon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/90233801"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T13:10:20Z","content":"Abortions are a necessary option in women's health. We have the right to access this legal service should we need to. We are one of only two provinces who do not have abortions covered under medicare. How is that ok? We are also one of the lower income provinces with the highest rates of unemployment. Access to abortions at no Cost is necessary and is the case for the rest of canada. Nb needs to have the same services offered. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lindsay  Sherwood","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/5110042"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T16:15:37Z","content":"Women in Canada have the right to choose, and closing this clinic is only going to cause women to find unsafe alternatives for pregnancy termination. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cameron Reid","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/60854989"},{"created_at":"2014-05-02T15:16:02Z","content":"Because, simply, it is the right thing to do !","like_count":0,"author_name":"Paul R Davis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6938802"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T15:58:46Z","content":"Women's rights and the right to abortion should be made accessible and the government should be removing barriers rather than putting them in place","like_count":0,"author_name":"Matthew Numer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89626391"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T02:19:37Z","content":"every person needs health care","like_count":0,"author_name":"Patty Phillips","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/65512135"},{"created_at":"2014-03-16T13:21:27Z","content":"I believe this is a fundamental human rights.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Benjamin Roundell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86044709"},{"created_at":"2014-04-17T23:13:49Z","content":"All women in Canada should have equitable access to abortion.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marcella Jones","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/49876228"},{"created_at":"2014-03-21T00:38:26Z","content":"I think it's important for women in any situation to be able to choose what they do, and they shouldn't have to deal with more stress by not having options or support.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Patrick Hare","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86780187"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T15:56:24Z","content":"Women's health and the right to choose are part of our basic, essential rights and these services should stay in the province.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Katie Rourke","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/61150183"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T14:10:51Z","content":"Woman have the rights to their own bodies","like_count":0,"author_name":"Phil Mercier","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89368503"}]}
