{"page":12,"prev_page_endpoint":"http://api.change.org/v1/petitions/1459961/reasons?page=11&page_size=500","next_page_endpoint":"http://api.change.org/v1/petitions/1459961/reasons?page_size=500","total_pages":5,"reasons":[]}
{"page":4,"prev_page_endpoint":"http://api.change.org/v1/petitions/1459961/reasons?page=3&page_size=500","next_page_endpoint":"http://api.change.org/v1/petitions/1459961/reasons?page=5&page_size=500","total_pages":5,"reasons":[{"created_at":"2014-04-14T23:56:55Z","content":"If abortions are going to be unable to be accessed then there should also be a law prohibiting men from leaving women after they get them pregnant. Because if a women can't back out of having a child, a man shouldn't be able to either.\r\n\r\nThis isn't the 1950's. The decision to close this clinic is a step back in time and makes me disgraced to be Canadian. My rights are not up for debate. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kimberly Drisdelle","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12703303"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T15:22:25Z","content":"Qu'on soit d'accord ou non avec le principe de l'avortement, tout le monde devrait y avoir droit.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gabriel Robichaud","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/60811437"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T19:56:07Z","content":"The constitution","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tina Desjardins","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36003426"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T20:55:52Z","content":"It is imensely important for women to have the choice to get this procedure done.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Evan Furness","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89485810"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T12:50:30Z","content":"This should be a service covered by medicare with less restrictions","like_count":0,"author_name":"Calvin Taylor","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89617750"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T00:28:31Z","content":"Why do people not realize that abortions will continue to happen whether they are funded or not, but having them supervised by proper healthcare providers will just ensure the safety of the woman having it done?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jami Turner","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/70473304"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T04:52:20Z","content":"Because It is OK to hold your own views, but you cannot force them upon others. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christie Ings","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85131406"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T12:53:06Z","content":"Because it is a fundamental equality right.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Noella Richard","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/77441808"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T16:22:06Z","content":"The illusion that the right to a safe abortion is strictly a moral choice needs to end. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"diane edison","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58102008"},{"created_at":"2014-03-09T21:31:43Z","content":"Because it is a necessary right to have full control over your own body.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Pat Neill","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47051878"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T20:12:56Z","content":"For easy access to those who need it. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lorraine McMackin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89659857"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T22:34:31Z","content":"As a young NB woman concerned with the range of health options available to  New Brunswick women, I want the government to reconsider its decision not to fund or subsidize abortion services.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Caterina Corazza","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/64960631"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T23:03:42Z","content":"Access to healthcare and reproductive choice is a right. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"emily hudson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27188222"},{"created_at":"2014-03-17T14:52:09Z","content":"Because what the NB government is enforcing is illegal and we need to call them out on their actions.  New Brunswick does not get to opt out of national legal decisions. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Terri Breen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/86274437"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T17:12:05Z","content":"equal access to health care across Canada","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jessica Yeates","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89471084"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T11:44:51Z","content":"I live in an area where teen pregnancy is a growing occurance. I have a daughter who I had in high school because it was my choice. But by closing one of the most important institutions around here, other young girls will have that choice taken away. Government funding shouldn't have taken this long to be recognized for something so important for womens rights. Everyone should have the oportunity to a safe and affordable (if possible, cost free) abortion. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jill Pomeroy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89356163"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T20:16:36Z","content":"Because, having access to an abortion should not even be a question. This is a right that we're - all women - supposed to have. Paying close to 800$ for an abortion is outrageous, seriously how do we expect poor women to get out of poverty? Either you come up with 800 bucks right now or get even poorer because you'll have to take care of an other human being even if it's wasn't your choice. I mean it's so ironic, medications like Viagra or Cialis are covered by health care but abortion is not...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Fran\u00e7ois Alexandra","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/82975910"},{"created_at":"2014-03-27T19:13:36Z","content":"It's one of the only places women from PEI have close access to, since there are no clinics here on the Island. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rebecca Chapman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87592168"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T17:45:38Z","content":"This is an essential right. Stop whining about our declining population, and how to stem the tide, while implementing BACKWARDS POLICY.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Erik Moore","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/41014984"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:10:23Z","content":"Do you really need to ask why this is important to me? Women deserve the right to choose, not the right to beg two doctors to sign off on a totally legal procedure.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brittany Lauton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89374003"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T18:54:10Z","content":"it is a womend s right to choose to have an abortion.","like_count":0,"author_name":"kim dawson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85194966"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T21:47:51Z","content":"Autonomy, freedom of choices\r\nEquality in care and availability of services.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Annie Lajoie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89290172"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T18:45:35Z","content":"I believe women should have the right to choose","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Densmore","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89646406"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T19:19:00Z","content":"Permitting religious foolishness to interfere with women's health is sick.The government should fund abortion services in full.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Myles MacLean","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36103306"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T22:06:15Z","content":"We need safe and accessible abortion options for women in New Brunswick. It is disheartening that this hasn't been the case for so long. There is no such thing as no abortions. There is only safe or unsafe abortions. We need to make this happen for the health and safety for women in this province.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amber Yates","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89556656"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T16:45:24Z","content":"Because New-Brunswick is not the third world","like_count":0,"author_name":"Martin H\u00e9tu","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89469191"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T07:29:53Z","content":"Because I'm a woman and a Canadian, and believe that the government of New Brunswick has the responsibility to respect not only women's right to choose, but also the Supreme Court's determination that individuals have the right to determine when and where to bear children. ","like_count":0,"author_n