 MacDonald","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/5146076"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T00:07:44Z","content":"The New Brunswick government is VIOLATING women's constitutional rights. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Olivia Flynn-Gomez","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89561541"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T11:38:02Z","content":"Because it is the right thing to do.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Simms","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89449701"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T00:25:33Z","content":"20 yrs ago the idea of women having the right to determine their own reproduction was clearly stated in international documents for the first time. It is gravely concerning that we are moving backwards instead of forward regarding women's rights.  This is not about religion or personal beliefs and values, this is about human rights and upholding the law. It seems like a no-brainer that our governments should support human rights, regrettably it appears they do not.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amber Young","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/71311021"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T18:58:08Z","content":"Rights must be protected and enforced. It's shameful of a government to do this.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Olivier Savoie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89477764"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:15:28Z","content":"Freedom. It's my body. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hannah Titus","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/46548950"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T17:14:57Z","content":"Reproductive health care, including abortion, is a human right. Paying for reproductive services limits reproductive rights.","like_count":0,"author_name":"PhebeAnn Wolframe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3272712"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T16:13:31Z","content":"It isn't right to use legislation/funding (or lack thereof) to diminish ones ability to choose their destiny. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michael Colpitts","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3576347"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T23:36:08Z","content":"because every woman has a right to choice what is right for her body. Specially depending how or why things came to pass. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alaurea Ainsworth","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/14540338"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T07:43:02Z","content":"New Brunswick is choosing to take a big step back into the past. Not surprised, but disappointed. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ashley Krista Furrow","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89598960"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T12:55:52Z","content":"Across Canada the battle has been won to make Abortion legal. There is no reason for the red tape involved or qualifications on the funding for the bare minimum of clinics in New Brunswick","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ryan Cashion","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89730115"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T16:53:39Z","content":"It bothers me that there are many elected officials (across all parties) who believe in the \"worst case scenario\" when it comes to every social issue, and because of this, social change is continuously stymied. They have this vision of women everywhere getting abortions all the time as if it were a simple decision; as if women actually want to have abortions. Thankfully I will never have to make that decision, but I feel nothing but compassion for those who do. The lack of government support for women who need it is a blatant slap in the face which will continue to alienate women from their province and perhaps their country. This isn't just an issue for women. This is an issue everyone should be concerned with. Sometimes \"medically necessary\" means that you have made a decision not to bring up a child in the current conditions you are in because you know that child would have less opportunities...especially if it's a girl.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jake MacDonald","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58823492"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T21:14:10Z","content":"Everyone should have a choice whether to become a parent. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"erella ganon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/20408749"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T17:57:33Z","content":"Women deserve to at least have options about what to do with their body, regardless of anyone else's opinion on what is right and wrong","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kelsey Witherly","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89639942"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T21:48:16Z","content":"it is a constitutional right and I also support a woman's right to choose.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Terri Lyn Hall","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/87061810"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T22:50:07Z","content":"I'm about to move to Fredericton.  Access to reproductive health care is essential.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kristi Allain","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45455704"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T22:55:02Z","content":"Because women deserve a choice. If men can walk out on a pregnancy then women should be able to also. We should decide what happens to our bodies and to our lives.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Vanessa LeBlanc","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89300989"},{"created_at":"2014-03-19T22:16:50Z","content":"This shouldn't even be a question, every woman has the right to make her own decision about what she does with her body and the choices of that decision should not be taken away from her. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Danielle Marie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3065455"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T02:22:07Z","content":"Because women should have a choice, especially those that have been raped or abused by family members!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Patti  Gordon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16882483"},{"created_at":"2014-04-17T23:11:33Z","content":"It is every women's right to have this choice, and to have a safe and accessible place to do so.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jocelyn Allaby","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/90041564"},{"created_at":"2014