t":0,"author_name":"Megan Cornish","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/731590"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T01:34:04Z","content":"It is not for me to judge.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Helene Justason","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89564758"},{"created_at":"2014-03-24T19:41:09Z","content":"I support EQUAL, non-discriminatory access to safe, legal abortion for ALL Canadian women. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lin Burman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/64794087"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T03:14:41Z","content":"Every woman has the right to have the support to make their own decisions.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hanna Donovan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89692183"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T03:28:07Z","content":"Men shouldn't be controlling women's bodies!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ian Nicholson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8209450"},{"created_at":"2014-04-17T11:40:32Z","content":"Safe and timely access to abortions offered in a caring and non-judgmental environment is essential for women in this province. The current situation puts women in New Brunswick in an unequal and unjust position compared to women across this country.  That has got to change now, along with our health system's overall approach to women's health - which needs to be much improved.","like_count":0,"author_name":"David Coon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89992816"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T18:56:26Z","content":"choice","like_count":0,"author_name":"William Ogilvie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89545909"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T00:43:59Z","content":"Every women deserves control of their bodies and access to the services she needs!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Joanie Herron","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37950766"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T02:28:29Z","content":"This is about human rights, not majority opinion. With the amount of people on welfare in our provide, with multiple child households, this should be encouraged if families cannot support themselves, let alone have the province support a family.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Randi Gallant","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47837618"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T00:29:05Z","content":"Every Canadian should have access to a service which is needed, and legal. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Claire Barr\u00e9","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/57257142"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T01:01:23Z","content":"This is a matter that should not be taken lightly.  However, all women should have the right to choose what happens to their bodies.  Why should politicians be able to enforce a law regarding a matter they have no knowledge about.  No male politician will ever be in this situation in relation to their own body.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Barbara Isenor","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89563531"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T12:21:01Z","content":"This is about a woman's right to chose, sometimes accidents happen. They shouldnt be forced to have a child and bear the financial burden if they chose not to.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kelsey Henderson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78448030"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T17:36:24Z","content":"It is horrendous that this amazing clinic will likely have to close its doors when an absolutely despicable 'Women's Care Center' will be allowed to remain open right next door. Reproductive Rights are an asset and necessity to any thriving, progressive location. By ending government funding to this amazing location, we are taking a massive step backwards in the rights of women.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amanda Coneen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56725700"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T22:04:16Z","content":"Today I was reminded of my embarrassment for New Brunswick - particularly the silence from the government and the official opposition on this important issue.\r\nHow does this province expect to join the rest of the country in the 21st century if they are still restricting a woman's access to reproductive healthcare?\r\nNo wonder so many youth have turned away from New Brunswick - it is clear that it's government does not share the values of young people and instead embrace an antiquated (and unconstitutional) opinion on the rights of women.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alex MacDonald","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89292622"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T20:02:55Z","content":"for the women who have the right to chose to bring a child into this world or not","like_count":0,"author_name":"Emilie Gray","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85332572"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T18:38:38Z","content":"because I don't like policies and laws that pertain to religion.  Also it is up to a Woman and no body else!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mr. KELLY SELWAH","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89763823"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T19:01:05Z","content":"Women's rights are human rights.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carla Barton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29973043"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T22:21:46Z","content":"Because no child should come into this world unwanted, and those who aren't prepared to raise children should have to choice not to.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Fin Mackay-Boyce","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85350968"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T14:13:01Z","content":"This clinic allows women not only from New Brunswick but also from Prince Edward Island and some parts of Nova Scotia to access safe abortion.\r\nThis is 2014, women should no longer have to raid their coat closets to find a solution to an unfortunate situation. \r\nMy uterus, my choice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cailyn Bean","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89459522"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T17:01:55Z","content":"Reproductive health is a basic need for all women. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Joey Hartman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7510073"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T12:07:29Z","content":"It is essential for the women of NB to have a safe place to have an abortion if they so choose. Women should not be forced to jump through hoops seeking approval from two doctors in order to \"be allowed\" to have one. Referral delays, anti-choice doctors and the added stress of this process is demeaning and unnecessary. Woman should not be forced into carrying a child to term simply because she cannot afford an abortion or her doctor will not sign off on one. We need this.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jenn Booth","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/79093801"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T13:06:00Z","content":"Fundamental part of Women's Rights.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jason Sonier","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13658070"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T18:19:28Z","content":"this is something I commented on a debate on Facebook about this issue: \r\nNo one has yet been successful in convincing people to not have sex. Like it or not, people have always had sex for reasons other than procreation. Even in times where there were strict, strict moral codes against it. Keep fighting the good fight, though. It's easy to say \"just don't do it\". You are NEVER going to convince people of that. Parents have tried since the dawn of time to stop their children from having premarital sex, and has that worked? OBVIOUSLY NOT. You are kidding yourself if you think it ever will. I don't think any child should have to be born into this world unwanted. You may say \"adoption is an option\", but no full-grown woman should be forced to give up her bodily autonomy. The second a woman (an already living, breathing, out in the world HUMAN BEING) becomes pregnant, she matters not- all that matters is the small clump of cells inside her. People are not saying it should have \"equal rights\", they are saying it should TRUMP the rights of the mother. They are saying a fetus is having the right to use someone else's body. No. Just no. No one has the right to do that.\r\n\r\nI went to the Body World discovery museum in new york recently and I saw in an exhibit there, an actual fertilized sperm and egg behind glass . Want to know what it looks like? NOTHING. Like a speck of dust !!! It is not a human being, and if a full grown person doesn't want that inside them, doesn't want to be forced to go through pregnancy, SHE SHOULD NOT HAVE TO. End of story.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Katherine V","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10001183"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T19:38:56Z","content":"I strongly believe in a womans right to terminate a pregnancy until the time that the fetus would be able to live outside her body but of course as early as possible after conception. This clinic is unfortunately the best option for women of the Atantic provinces at this time although it should be fully funded and free to users.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Anna Holdaway","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89772627"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T18:48:12Z","content":"Women have the right to economic and physical autonomy, for which access to safe, publicly-funded abortion services is necessary. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Templeton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89545421"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T04:14:58Z","content":"Womans' rights are human rights- this includes the right to choose whether to terminate a pregnancy.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Isabella Yachimec","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/60750112"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T20:51:33Z","content":"I believe not every girl or woman is in the right situation when she has an unwanted pregnancy. I think they should be able to make the right choice for themselves and their families. If this clinic closes, the unemployment rate will probably go up because of this. This closure will not be good for the maritimes.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chylynn Brideau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89552591"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T23:59:25Z","content":"Women should have the right to choose what happens with their bodies. Men have no idea what it's like to bear an unwanted child. It's easy to oppose and comment on something that doesn't really affect you. In the end the child suffers. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Eden LeBlanc","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85359736"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T07:31:15Z","content":"I support the right to choose without prejudice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jamie Rose","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/71864599"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T12:15:05Z","content":"These are our rights as women! It is 2014 and this should not even be an issue at present day! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Keltie Keir","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89358579"},{"created_at":"2014-05-06T22:16:33Z","content":"I spent almost 15 years in the 70/80s era working to give equal and fair access for all women in Canada to the right to  choose and get the services they needed for a safe abortion should that be their choice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Catherine Daw","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91823933"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T21:58:27Z","content":"This is important to me because every women has the right to make a choice that is right for them concerning their bodies and when that choice is made they need somewhere they can go to have the procedure.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amanda Brown","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89556277"},{"created_at":"2014-03-19T23:36:39Z","content":"Because there is another petition banning funding to the clinic and living in New Brunswick that just isn't right ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Danielle Marie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3065455"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T12:45:48Z","content":"I support any woman's right to reproductive choice.  It 's not a man's damn business.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kenn Chaplin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1948065"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T16:13:00Z","content":"A young woman in the position to choose an abort