ave the right to choose and the government should not look the other way by saying the 2 doctor referral is the only route available. It is a sad day when NB and Atlantic Canadian women's fundamental rights takes a leap back. ...Trust me, if men could get pregnant, this would not be an issue.","like_count":0,"author_name":"David C.","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2067802"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T20:49:40Z","content":"Letting women to the rights to their own bodies is important and taking this clinic away will be denying women of these rights.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kalie Mallaley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89664868"},{"created_at":"2014-04-22T13:45:26Z","content":"Women have de right to decide if they commit themselves with maternity","like_count":0,"author_name":"ariane gauthier-tremblay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36285269"},{"created_at":"2014-03-26T21:11:58Z","content":"ONLY contraception can save the world, or your school district.  Please sign these petitions advocating municipal environmental\r\ncontraception funding, which is increasingly politically realistic due\r\nto The Big Sort in more and more towns, and helps women's rights, quality of life, and school taxes as well as being at\r\nleast 5 times more cost-effective than any other environmental effort.\r\n<a href=\"http://www.change.org/petitions/view/transfer_all_environmental_funds_to_contraception\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.change.org/petitions/view/transfer_all_environmental_funds_to_contraception</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.arhp.org/publications-and-resources/contraception-journal/january-2014\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.arhp.org/publications-and-resources/contraception-journal/january-2014</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.change.org/members/218464\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.change.org/members/218464</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.feminist.org/news/newsbyte/uswirestory.asp?id=12874\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.feminist.org/news/newsbyte/uswirestory.asp?id=12874</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.thepetitionsite.com/1/transfer-all-environmental-funds-to-contraception-especially-municipal/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.thepetitionsite.com/1/transfer-all-environmental-funds-to-contraception-especially-municipal/</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.arhp.org/publications-and-resources/contraception-journal/january-2014\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.arhp.org/publications-and-resources/contraception-journal/january-2014</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.nyc.gov/html/doh/html/living/condoms-where.shtml\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.nyc.gov/html/doh/html/living/condoms-where.shtml</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/alan.ditmore\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.facebook.com/alan.ditmore</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://secure.prochoiceamerica.org/site/Advocacy?cmd=display&amp;page=UserAction&amp;id=5319\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://secure.prochoiceamerica.org/site/Advocacy?cmd=display&page=UserAction&id=5319</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://nwhn.org/newsletter/node/1383\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://nwhn.org/newsletter/node/1383</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://action.biologicaldiversity.org/p/dia/action/public/?action_KEY=5999\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://action.biologicaldiversity.org/p/dia/action/public/?action_KEY=5999</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.change.org/petitions/tell_web_forum_administrators_to_stop_censoring_overpopulation_activists_and_lying_about_reasons\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.change.org/petitions/tell_web_forum_administrators_to_stop_censoring_overpopulation_activists_and_lying_about_reasons</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.change.org/petitions/asheville-lgbt-rights-for-environment\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.change.org/petitions/asheville-lgbt-rights-for-environment</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://groups.yahoo.com/group/childfreetown/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://groups.yahoo.com/group/childfreetown/</a>\r\n\r\nThe prochoice and contraception movements are placing too high a priority on defensive actions in the red states when we should be going on the offensive, the side of \"change\", in the blue states, and cities. The worst places\r\nwill get even worse no matter what we do, but the unrealized political potential, the low hanging fruit, is in making the best places even better. This opportunity is being caused by The Big Sort, <a href=\"http://www.thebigsort.com/maps.php\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.thebigsort.com/maps.php</a> .  Mayors are not answerable to rural voters, unlike governors and presidents.\r\nProchoice churches like the UU church, Presbyterian Church USA, and Anglican Church may consider overpopulation their purview and responsibility to make up for the damage done by pronatalist churches by making use of PopOffsetts:\r\n<a href=\"http://www.popoffsets.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.popoffsets.com/</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.feminist.org/news/newsbyte/uswirestory.asp?id=12891\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.feminist.org/news/newsbyte/uswirestory.asp?id=12891</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://secure.ppaction.org/site/Advocacy?cmd=display&amp;page=UserAction&amp;id=12828\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://secure.ppaction.org/site/Advocacy?cmd=display&page=UserAction&id=12828</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.amplifyyourvoice.org/end_abonly\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.amplifyyourvoice.org/end_abonly</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=5041388\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=5041388</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.change.org/petitions/mayor-esther-manheimer-of-asheville-nc-support-marriage-equality-sign-the-mayors-for-freedom-to-marry-pledge\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.change.org/petitions/mayor-esther-manheimer-of-asheville-nc-support-marriage-equality-sign-the-mayors-for-freedom-to-marry-pledge</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.change.org/petitions/repeal-and-or-ban-all-single-family-zoning-and-unit-density-limits\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.change.org/petitions/repeal-and-or-ban-all-single-family-zoning-and-unit-density-limits</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.change.org/petitions/the-president-of-the-united-states-guarantee-the-right-to-sleep-in-public\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.change.org/petitions/the-president-of-the-united-states-guarantee-the-right-to-sleep-in-public</a>\r\nWe americans love cars more than babies, Very soon we will have to choose, and we will choose cars.\r\nPopoffsets almost has it right except that local contraception funding can solve local environmental problems like traffic, school tax;\r\n and landfill, water and sewer treatment capacity.  So environmental contraception funding is not just global or long term.  Prenatal care adds to local traffic in mere months.\r\n<a href=\"http://www.projectprevention.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.projectprevention.org/</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.freetownproject.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.freetownproject.com/</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.news.com.au/world/hillary-clinton-tries-to-silence-brave-bindi/story-fndir2ev-1226560803039\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.news.com.au/world/hillary-clinton-tries-to-silence-brave-bindi/story-fndir2ev-1226560803039</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://populationaction.org/newsletters/prioritizing-gender-and-climate-change-in-municipal-budgets-in-the-philippines/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://populationaction.org/newsletters/prioritizing-gender-and-climate-change-in-municipal-budgets-in-the-philippines/</a>\r\nIf you can't win significant (over 5% of budget) environmental contraception funding from your city hall,\r\n then get a moving van and move to a town where you CAN WIN!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alan Ditmore","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/218464"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T11:28:42Z","content":"Reproductive rights are important. It is also important that we have consistency in medical policy nationwide","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stephen Tobias","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89611544"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:24:44Z","content":"Because we deserve the right to make our own decision, not have it made for us ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alexie Dunnett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3588425"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:48:06Z","content":"Access to safe and legal abortions will prevent women from taking dangerous measures to try an abortion at home, and having a wanted and planned pregnancy helps secure a childs future wellbeing and education","like_count":0,"author_name":"Katherine Verhoeven","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30997862"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:57:55Z","content":"it's a woman's right to choose and no one has the right to take that away.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Aviva Attis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7866262"},{"created_at":"2014-03-15T16:18:16Z","content":"all women deserve access to all medical services","like_count":0,"author_name":"wesley kellar","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/46260315"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T21:36:11Z","content":"This service needs to be covered under medicare. By not making this available to women when they want it, NB government is violating the Canada Health Act (accessibility). Chief Justice Brian Dickson wrote: \"Forcing a woman, by threat of criminal sanction to carry a fetus to term unless she meets certain criteria unrelated to her own priorities and aspirations, is a profound interference with a woman's body and thus a violation of her security of the person.\" ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jensa Arseneau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89488075"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T12:14:57Z","content":"because we want people to be able to make their choices and abortion is highly influential on women's empowerment, event just to know that it's a possibility.","like_count":0,"author_name":"maude caron","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16113800"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T14:29:03Z","content":"As I said to a friend, I'm all for pro choice but not pro abortion. Why? Abortion isn't the right choice for everyone. I don't ever want someone to be forced to have an abortion that doesn't want to or can't live with themselves afterwards, but those who can and deem it a requirement should have the access and ability to.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Matthew Ryder","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85421792"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T17:48:01Z","content":"Women's rights are kind of important... I don't see why our government should be able to get away with this kind of wholesale discrimination.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ian Sawlor","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89387407"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T18:42:13Z","content":"Abortion access is a fundamental right for women; legislators should not be subversively restricting women's reproductive rights, particularly when that legislation undermines the decisions already made decades ago by the Canadian Supreme Court.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stephanie Pettigrew","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85323054"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T01:46:01Z","content":"What I'm I paying taxes for? Not for women's rights to be neglected that's for sure.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lindsay Kovalik","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89421678"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T22:03:11Z","content":"EVERY woman deserves the right the chose!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lindsay McLeod","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85349027"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T02:47:45Z","content":"I think us as woman have the right to do what we want with our bodies.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ashleigh Howe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/75616780"},{"created_at":"2014-04-17T23:31:14Z","content":"I feel women's reproductive rights in my home province severely lacking. Time to get with the 21st century.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Scott Farris","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/90043158"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T18:20:12Z","content":"It's not a decision to be made by uninvolved people.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Damian Nevers","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89390366"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T18:39:14Z","content":"As a woman, I believe in the right to make my own decisions about my reproductive life. I enjoyed living in New Brunswick, but this issue was always a sore spot for me, and embarrassing for the province.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Melissa Normandeau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85322675"},{"created_at":"2014-04-15T17:34:05Z","content":"Women should have a choice!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ryan Hunziker","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89755038"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T23:28:20Z","content":"Because I am a woman.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Celia Thompson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11673000"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T18:20:07Z","content":"Abortion is a legal and safe way to terminate a pregnancy, and yet abortion rights in this country are being eroded almost daily.  The closure of the clinic further limits the accessibility of abortions to women who need them and will ultimately force women back into back alleys, unsafe procedures, inadvertent sterility due to improper procedures, and even death. Is the message here that this is what we deserve if we become pregnant in New Brunswick and wish, for ANY reason, to exercise our LEGAL right to choose?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bobbi Zahra","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2095986"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T23:44:23Z","content":"Because the government shouldn't be taking two steps back on women's rights. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Melana Currie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89308960"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T22:08:29Z","content":"a woman's choice to do what she thinks is right for her,no one else should make that decision","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dianne Keating","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/68710850"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T03:20:55Z","content":"This is a Canadian right for women, that has been firmly established and recognized.  It is beyond time that it should be a uniform facet of this Country.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Scott Strong","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/33059108"},{"created_at":"2014-04-26T21:25:27Z","content":"Abortion is a women's right","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kaitlyn Ackert","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/77487826"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T16:24:54Z","content":"I rather suspect that it costs more for women to have two doctors' appointments and travel to hospitals for surgery, than for medicare to pay for the procedure at a private clinic.  Regardless, the government has no business making these decisions for women.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cheryl Petreman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/61816967"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T17:00:01Z","content":"Almost all of my friends have kids over the age of one or are currently pregnant and I'm only eighteen. Those numbers would double. If something like this was shut down It could cause a lot of damage ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Madisyn Spence","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89383323"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T15:39:44Z","content":"Access to safe abortion saves lives. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Erin Wilsone","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3592076"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T04:04:49Z","content":"Women should have an option, it is their bodies. What about someone that got raped? Has to be pregnant for 9 months with each day reminding her of it???","like_count":0,"author_name":"Katrina Bird","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6451816"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T20:50:01Z","content":"Women should have the right to choose. The government has no right to tell women what to do with their bodies. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Francis Waters","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89282027"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T18:39:41Z","content":"Women have the right to accessible abortions. It saves lives and women have the right to choose. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kristi Keenan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89645651"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T22:07:48Z","content":"Women should have safe choices.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Valerie Tiller","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89556738"},{"created_at":"2014-04-22T15:06:04Z","content":"Un droit fondamental","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sophie Pomerleau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/21828562"},{"created_at":"2014-04-16T22:42:10Z","content":"I am a mother of two young women, I want to make sure they will get to have the choice as I did (in another province)","like_count":0,"author_name":"Heather Moxon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56873377"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T14:24:56Z","content":"I am a woman","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kate Olmstead","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85166842"},{"created_at":"2014-03-10T18:25:11Z","content":"Access to abortion is a human rights issue and New Brunswick is not upholding a standard.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Heidi Boudreau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85190330"},{"created_at":"2014-05-13T06:32:01Z","content":"Abortion is legal all across Canada and is already regulated in New Brunswick by the CPSNB. The current situation in New Brunswick is disturbingly paternalistic, a women should not have to get the approval of two Drs who say an abortion is medically necessary. Restricting a woman's ability to control her own reproductive health is not in line with the laws of Canada or our Charter of Rights. It discriminates against low income women and those who need an abortion for non-medical reasons. There are many very good non-medical reasons for a woman to get an abortion.\r\n\r\nForcing a woman to give birth to a child against her will is inexcusable and a violation of the laws of Canada and our Charter of Rights. The New Brusnwick gov't must end this discriminatory behaviour and fully fund abortions at clinics as well as dropping the requirement for the abortion to be medically necessary with two Drs approval. \r\n\r\nNo Canadian woman should still have to fight for their reproductive rights in this day and age. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rich Reist","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/655367"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T20:02:42Z","content":"Because human rights.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Julie St-Pierre","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89275235"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T19:17:36Z","content":"We need a clinic in New Brunswick as it serves PEI as well. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"melissa lowthers","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89395276"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T14:33:00Z","content":"It is absolutely essential that in a free society, women have complete control over their own bodies. Full stop.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brian Lowry","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/50192207"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T19:17:42Z","content":"This is a human rights issue, taking this away is a breach! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Julie McKenzie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89650369"},{"created_at":"2014-04-12T00:41:24Z","content":"I am a Nurse and I believe it's important for the patient to have the right of any decision they make.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bruce Parsons","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8158629"},{"created_at":"2014-03-11T20:34:44Z","content":"Women in New Brunswick need rights equal to, minimally, women in the rest of Canada. The right to choose should be just that. It's not 'the right to pay to choose\".","like_count":0,"author_name":"Liz MacDougall","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8161515"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T23:06:21Z","content":"It's a must-have for all women. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gill Phillips","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89559196"},{"created_at":"2014-04-13T23:26:38Z","content":"Women need to have control of their bodies and when and whether or not they bear children.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jake Peters","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22160615"},{"created_at":"2014-03-12T01:05:28Z","content":"Any woman who makes this choice is doing it for reasons unbeknownst to anyone else. In the long term, regardless of the reason, the government may end up paying for something as a result. If the person can not afford the procedure they may take poor care of themselves and an unhealthy child might be born,  this person may need social assistance, low income housing, go into bankruptcy among many other possibilities. Taking away rights always have repercussions! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kassandra Vale","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/85364437"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T11:09:42Z","content":"Freedom of choice","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennifer Caddell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29698781"},{"created_at":"2014-04-16T04:05:14Z","content":"i feel it is a womans right and choice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Robin Rees","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/57461237"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T15:28:08Z","content":"This is important to me because no one has the right to tell a woman what she can or can't do with her own body! This would be a huge step back in women's rights for the women of NB!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Janice Tupper","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2214422"},{"created_at":"2014-04-11T15:20:24Z","content":"As somebody who grew up in Bathurst, I urge my home province to stop these discriminatory and backward practices against women who want/need abortions.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Diane Wilson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89182686"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T15:33:42Z","content":"it is important for every mother to be a willing mother, every child a wanted child.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amanda Pottle","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89623577"},{"created_at":"2014-04-10T20:28:52Z","content":"Human right.  Access to health care.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brian Sullivan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89279023"},{"created_at":"2014-04-14T19:39:18Z","content":"I believe I should be able